(80, 'overview', '<p><b>What is MSME Registration?</b></p><p>\r\n\r\nMicro, Small, and Medium Enterprises (MSME) is an acronym for MSME. MSME industries are the backbone of the economy in a growing country like India. When these industries grow, the country\'s economy grows and thrives as a whole. We can also call it small-scale industries, or SSIs. An applicant can apply for an MSME loan based on the annual revenue of his or her firm by evaluating loan offers from multiple financial institutions and filling out and submitting online loan application forms. Applicants can apply for MSME registration by paying a minimal fees and filling up an online application. Let\'s go over MSME registration in more detail, including the actions and processes involved, as well as other relevant information. On October 2, 2006, the MSME became functioning. It was established in order to assist micro, small, and medium-sized enterprises in becoming more competitive by promoting, facilitating, and improving their competitiveness.</p>', '84', '2021-11-16 09:59:44', '2021-11-16 23:27:08'),
(81, 'details', '<div><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\"><b>Advantages of MSME Registration</b></span></div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem; letter-spacing: 0.0312rem;\">Below are few of the advantages of MSME Registration:</span><br></div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem; letter-spacing: 0.0312rem;\">Because the interest rate is relatively low, about 1 to 1.5 percent, bank loans become cheaper as a result of MSME registration. These loans have much lower interest rates than traditional loans.</span><br></div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem; letter-spacing: 0.0312rem;\">Instead of ten years, minimum alternative tax (MAT) credits can now be carried forward for up to 15 years.</span><br></div><div><br></div><div>Once registered, the cost of acquiring a patent or starting a business is reduced thanks to a variety of reductions and concessions.</div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem; letter-spacing: 0.0312rem;\">Because the Udyam Registration Portal is integrated with the Government e-Marketplace and numerous other State Government websites that offer easy access to their marketplaces and e-tenders, MSME registration makes it easier to receive government tenders.</span><br></div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem; letter-spacing: 0.0312rem;\">There is a One-Time Settlement Fee for delinquent MSME payments.</span><br></div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem; letter-spacing: 0.0312rem;\">The Udyam Registration will assist MSMEs in taking advantage of government initiatives such as the Credit Guarantee Scheme, Credit Linked Capital Subsidy Scheme, Public Procurement Policy, and Payment Delay Protection, among others.</span><br></div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem; letter-spacing: 0.0312rem;\">Banks are willing to lend to MSMEs as a priority sector.</span><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem; letter-spacing: 0.0312rem;\"><br></span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem; letter-spacing: 0.0312rem;\">MSMEs are eligible for a government security deposit waiver, which is beneficial when competing in e-tenders.</span><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem; letter-spacing: 0.0312rem;\">In a single Registration, any number of activities, including service, manufacturing, or both, can be added or described.</span><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem; letter-spacing: 0.0312rem;\">Subsidy for barcode registration.</span><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem; letter-spacing: 0.0312rem;\">Scheme to exclude people from paying direct taxes.</span><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem; letter-spacing: 0.0312rem;\">Reimbursement of ISO certification fees</span><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem; letter-spacing: 0.0312rem;\">Electricity bills are reduced.</span><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem; letter-spacing: 0.0312rem;\">In international trade exhibitions, special consideration is given.</span><br></div>', '84', '2021-11-16 09:59:44', '2021-11-16 23:27:08'),
(82, 'requirement', '<p>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         <b>MSME Eligibility Criteria:</b>\r\n</p><p>\r\nBecause the government has imposed a maximum revenue threshold, not all enterprises fit into the MSME category. To be classified as an MSME, a company must meet certain criteria.\r\n\r\nAccording to the MSMED Act of 2006, also known as the Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises Development Act.\r\n\r\nA manufacturing MSME can be identified if it meets the following criteria:\r\n\r\nMicro-enterprises — An investment of less than Rs 25 lakh is considered a micro-enterprise.\r\n\r\nSmall businesses — An investment of more than Rs 25 lakh but less than Rs 5 crore qualifies as a small business.\r\n\r\nMedium-sized businesses — Investments of more than Rs 5 crore but less than Rs 10 crore.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIn the service sector, an MSME can be identified if it meets the following criteria:\r\n\r\nMicro-enterprises — An investment of less than Rs 10 lakh is considered a micro-enterprise.\r\n\r\nSmall businesses — Investments of more than Rs 10 lakh but less than Rs 2 crore.\r\n\r\nMedium-sized businesses Have an investment of more than Rs 2 crore but less than Rs 5 crore.\r\n\r\nThe central government just modified the definition of MSME on the 13th of May 2020. An MSME is no longer defined just by its investments. FM Along with the premise of \"investment in plant and machinery,\" Nirmala Sitharaman has included \"annual turnover\" as an extra principle.\r\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    </p>', '84', '2021-11-16 09:59:44', '2021-11-16 23:27:08'),
(83, 'listicles', '<div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">MSME Eligibility Criteria:</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Because the government has imposed a maximum revenue threshold, not all enterprises fit into the MSME category. To be classified as an MSME, a company must meet certain criteria.</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">According to the MSMED Act of 2006, also known as the Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises Development Act.</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; 1 A manufacturing MSME can be identified if it meets the following criteria:</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; • Micro-enterprises — An investment of less than Rs 25 lakh is considered a micro-enterprise.</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; • Small businesses — An investment of more than Rs 25 lakh but less than Rs 5 crore qualifies as a small business.</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; • Medium-sized businesses — Investments of more than Rs 5 crore but less than Rs 10 crore.</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><br></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; 2 In the service sector, an MSME can be identified if it meets the following criteria:</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; • Micro-enterprises — An investment of less than Rs 10 lakh is considered a micro-enterprise.</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; • Small businesses — Investments of more than Rs 10 lakh but less than Rs 2 crore.</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; • Medium-sized businesses Have an investment of more than Rs 2 crore but less than Rs 5 crore.</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">The central government just modified the definition of MSME on the 13th of May 2020. An MSME is no longer defined just by its investments. FM Along with the premise of \"investment in plant and machinery,\" Nirmala Sitharaman has included \"annual turnover\" as an extra principle.</span></font></div>', '84', '2021-11-16 09:59:44', '2021-11-16 23:27:08'),
(84, 'regs', '<div><b>Documents required for MSME Registration</b></div><div><br></div><div>The only papers required for MSME registration are an Aadhaar Card and a PAN Card. MSME registration can be done totally online, with no documents verification needed. PAN and GST-linked information on investment and turnover would be automatically pulled from government databases through the Udyam Registration Portal. The Udyam Registration Portal is fully integrated with the Income Tax and GSTIN systems.</div><div><br></div><div>GST is optional for businesses that are not required to register under the GST statute. Businesses who are required to register for GST as part of the GST regime must first register for GST before applying for Udyam Registration.</div><div><br></div><div>Those who hold a UAM registration or any other registration issued by the Ministry of MSME will need to re-register at the Udyam Registration Portal by selecting \"For New Entrepreneurs who haven’t yet Registered as MSME or those with EM-II.\"</div><div><br></div><div>Enterprises with UAM registration must switch to Udyam Registration by December 31, 2021. Entrepreneurs with UAM registration who do not migrate to Udyam Registration by December 31, 2021 will lose their UAM registration and will no longer be eligible for MSMEs incentives.</div>', '84', '2021-11-16 09:59:44', '2021-11-16 23:27:08'),
(85, 'others', '<div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>What are the penalties that will be imposed for None-Filing of MSME-01?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>Non-compliance will result in a penalty and punishment under the Companies Act. Companies are required to file half-yearly returns in MSME Form 1 with the Registrar of Companies in respect of outstanding payments to micro and small businesses for goods and services supplied by them if the payment period exceeds 45 days from the date of acceptance or deemed acceptance, as per Section 405 (4) of the Companies Act, 2013.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>How to check MSME Registration status</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>To check the status using your name and registration number, follow the steps below:</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>Step 1: Applicants can monitor the status of their MSME application by going to the MSME registration official portal.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>Step 2: Applicants must input their 12-digit UAM number, followed by the captcha image\'s verification code.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>Step 3: To verify the status of your MSME registration online, click \'Verify.\'</b></span></font></div>', '84', '2021-11-16 09:59:44', '2021-11-16 18:33:48'),
(86, 'guide', '<div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>How to download or print MSME Registration Certificate</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>The following are the processes to obtain the registration certificate via the internet:</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>1st step: An applicant must go to https://udyamregistration.gov.in/UA/PrintAcknowledgement Pub.aspx to print their Udyog Aadhaar / MSME registration certificate.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>Step 2: The applicant must input his or her 12-digit UAM number, such as DL05A1234567.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>Step 3: As per the Udyog Aadhaar Certificate, the applicant must also input his or her mobile number.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>Step 4: Applicants can download or print their Udyog Aadhaar / MSME registration certificate after providing these details.</b></span></font></div>', '84', '2021-11-16 09:59:44', '2021-11-16 18:33:48'),
(87, 'faq', '<div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>FAQs:</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>How do I verify the status of my MSME registration?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>You will obtain a registration number after completing the registration process, which you will need for future reference. It usually takes 2-3 days for the total approval and registration procedure to be completed once you submit your form. You will receive your registration certificate through email.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>How long is MSME certificate in effect?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>The MSME certificate is valid for as long as the business is open for business. A provisional MSME certificate, on the other hand, is only valid for 5 years.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>What is the total cost to register as an MSME?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>The MSME registration process is absolutely costs some basic amount, unparalleled, and available online.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>What are the different kinds of MSME?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>MSMEs are divided into Manufacturing Enterprises and Service Enterprises under the Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises Development (MSMED) Act of 2006.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>What industries are covered by MSME?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>MSME regulates all manufacturing and service businesses.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>6. What is the maximum turnover for an MSME?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>* Micro-enterprise turnover limit: less than INR 5 crore * Small-enterprise turnover limit: INR 1 to 25 crore * Medium-enterprise turnover limit: INR 25 to 250 crore</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>7. Explain the difference between Udyog Aadhar and MSME/Udyog Registration?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Udyam Registration is a Ministry of Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises (MoMSMEs) approved by the Government of India MSME registration to start a business. MSME Aadhaar is for Small and Medium Enterprises provided by the Ministry of Small and Medium Enterprises (SMEs).</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>8. What are the chances of an online MSME application being rejected?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Low credit score, unpaid debts, loan defaults, low cash flow, absence of a business strategy, incomplete documentation, misleading information, and so on are all causes for MSME application rejection.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>9. Are banks willing to lend to MSME borrowers without requiring collateral?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Yes, they can acquire collateral-free loans if they take out unsecured business loans and have a strong CIBIL score, as well as a good financial and loan payback history. The rest is determined by the bank\'s qualifying conditions that must be met by the applicant.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>10. How long would it take for the MSME Certificate to be issued?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>The MSME Certificate is issued within 1-2 working days of the application being submitted.</b></span></font></div>', '84', '2021-11-16 09:59:44', '2021-11-16 18:33:48'),
(88, 'overview', '<b>What is FSSAI Registration?</b><br>\r\n\r\nThe Food Safety and Standards Authority of India (FSSAI) is the government organization in charge of overseeing and regulating the Indian food industry. An FSSAI Registration or License is required for everyone who manufactures, processes, stores, distributes, or sells food.\r\n\r\nThe 14-digit registration number for FSSAI indicates the producers as well as assembly state permit. The purpose of this registration method is to hold the FBO more accountable for maintaining the food products quality. The Food Safety and Standards (Licensing and Registration of Food Businesses) Regulations, 2011 is responsible for governing the licensing and registration process and standards.', '85', '2021-11-16 10:06:51', '2021-11-16 18:46:16'),
(89, 'details', '<p><b>Which types of organization requires FSSAI Registration?\r\n</b><br>\r\n\r\n\r\nFBOs who do the following types of business are needed to obtain an FSSAI Registration:\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\nRetail shops, such as, Snack Shops, Confectionery or Bakery Shops, and so on.\r\n\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nGol gappa stalls, chat stalls, fruits/vegetables vendors, Tea stalls, snacks stalls, Samosa stalls, Chinese food stalls, South Indian food stalls, sweet stalls, and so on are examples of temporary stalls.\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\nHawkers, who sell packaged or freshly prepared food while travelling around an area.\r\n\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nDairy Units such as Milk Chilling Units, Petty Milkmen, and Milk Vendors and etc.\r\n\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nUnits for the extraction and processing of vegetable oils.\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\nMeat markets, mutton markets, chicken markets, lamb markets, and so on are examples of slaughterhouses.\r\n\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nMeat and seafood processing facilities\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\nFood repackaging facilities are included in all food manufacturing/processing plants.\r\n\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nThere are two types of food which are proprietary food and novel food.\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nStorage facility that is cold/refrigerated.\r\n\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nFood product transporter with insulated refrigerated vans/wagons, milk tankers, food wagons, and food trucks, among other specialized vehicles.\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nHotels, restaurants, and bars are the other organizations which are available.</p>', '85', '2021-11-16 10:06:51', '2021-11-16 18:46:16'),
(90, 'requirement', '<b>Documents required for FSSAI Registration?\r\n<br></b>\r\nBelow is the list of documents required for FSSAI Registration.<br>\r\n\r\nAn application form that has been completed and signed in its entirety.<br>\r\n\r\nMake a food-safety management system a priority.<br>\r\n\r\nPassport sized photograph.<br>\r\n\r\nApplicant\'s proof of identity (Food Business Operator)<br>\r\n\r\nProperty ownership proof<br>\r\n\r\nProof of Business Address<br>\r\n\r\nProof of Lease Agreement<br>\r\n\r\nFood safety management system plan.<br>\r\n\r\nA list of the foods that will be used<br>\r\n\r\nIncorporation certificate<br>\r\n\r\nProcedure for obtaining FSSAI Registration.<br>\r\n\r\nBelow are the steps for obtaining FSSAI Registration.<br>\r\n\r\nFBOs can apply for FSSAI registration online by filling up either Form A or Form B on the FoSCoS site and submitting it. Another way by which FBOs can register is by submitting Form A or Form B to the Department of Food and Safety.<br>\r\n\r\nFBOs can apply for FSSAI registration online by filling out Form A (Registration Application) or Form B (State and Central License Application) on the FoSCoS website and submitting it. FBOs can also register with the Department of Food and Safety by submitting Form A or Form B, which must be accompanied by the necessary paperwork. \r\n<br>\r\nThe relevant documentation should be submitted along with the FSSAI registration form. The papers must be submitted to FoSCos online or personally presented to the Food and Safety Department with the application throughout the application process.\r\n<br>\r\nWithin 7 days of receiving an application, either physically or electronically through the FoSCoS portal, the Department can accept or reject the FSSAI registration form. In case the application is denied, the applicant should be notified in writing.\r\n<br>\r\nThe records will be examined by the Department.\r\n<br>\r\nIf necessary, the Department may undertake an examination of the food facilities prior to issuing the FSSAI registration certificate.\r\n<br>\r\nIf the FBO meets all of the requirements, the Department will issue an FSSAI registration certificate with the registration number and a snapshot of the applicant\'s email address. By logging into the FoSCoS portal, the applicant can also download the FSSAI registration certificate.\r\n<br>\r\nDuring business hours, the FSSAI registration certificate shall be conspicuously displayed at the FBO.', '85', '2021-11-16 10:06:51', '2021-11-16 18:46:16'),
(91, 'listicles', '<b>Benefits of FSSAI Registration?\r\n<br></b>\r\nObtaining a license can provide legal benefits, build goodwill, ensure food safety, increase customer awareness, and help a food business expand. It helps in regulating the manufacturing, storage, distribution, and sale of foods coming from outside. It is straightforward to raise cash from investors after an FBO is established with the FSSAI.\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nThe FSSAI logo on food products makes the customers believe that food is of high-quality. The FSSAI registration number on the food product is the proof that the establishment meets the required hygiene and quality requirements.', '85', '2021-11-16 10:06:51', '2021-11-16 18:46:16'),
(92, 'regs', '<b>Procedure for obtaining FSSAI Registration.<br></b>\r\n\r\nBelow are the steps for obtaining FSSAI Registration.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\nFBOs can apply for FSSAI registration online by filling up either Form A or Form B on the FoSCoS site and submitting it. Another way by which FBOs can register is by submitting Form A or Form B to the Department of Food and Safety.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\nFBOs can apply for FSSAI registration online by filling out Form A (Registration Application) or Form B (State and Central License Application) on the FoSCoS website and submitting it. FBOs can also register with the Department of Food and Safety by submitting Form A or Form B, which must be accompanied by the necessary paperwork. <br>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe relevant documentation should be submitted along with the FSSAI registration form. The papers must be submitted to FoSCos online or personally presented to the Food and Safety Department with the application throughout the application process.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\nWithin 7 days of receiving an application, either physically or electronically through the FoSCoS portal, the Department can accept or reject the FSSAI registration form. In case the application is denied, the applicant should be notified in writing.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe records will be examined by the Department.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\nIf necessary, the Department may undertake an examination of the food facilities prior to issuing the FSSAI registration certificate.\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nIf the FBO meets all of the requirements, the Department will issue an FSSAI registration certificate with the registration number and a snapshot of the applicant\'s email address. By logging into the FoSCoS portal, the applicant can also download the FSSAI registration certificate.\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nDuring business hours, the FSSAI registration certificate shall be conspicuously displayed at the FBO.\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nWhat are the consequences of Non- Compliance\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nAnyone who is registered or licenced with the FSSAI must adhere to the laws and regulations of the FSS Act. A food safety officer examines the facilities of the food business owner and utilises a checklist to evaluate compliance with applicable rules. Based on the level of compliance, the food safety officer issues a grade:\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nCompliance (C)\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nNon-compliance (NC)\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nPartial compliance (PC)\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nNot applicable/Not observed (NA)\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nUnder Section 32 of the FSS Act, 2006, the food safety officer may issue an improvement notice if appropriate. After giving the licensee an opportunity to show reason, the officer may suspend or revoke the license if the business operator fails to comply with the improvement notice. Any food business owner who has been affected by an improvement notice has the right to file a complaint with the state\'s food safety commissioner. The judgement can be challenged in the Food Safety Appellate Tribunal/High Court.', '85', '2021-11-16 10:06:51', '2021-11-16 18:46:16'),
(93, 'others', '<b>What is FSSAI Registration Cost?<br></b>\r\n\r\nThe Food Safety and Standards Regulations of 2011 established standards for the fee structure for Food Business Operators.<br>\r\n\r\nIn India, food firms must register with the Food Safety and Standards Authority of India (FSSAI), and those who do not must pay a fine.<br>\r\n\r\nThe FSSAI Registration Fee is split into two categories: government and expert. An application handling cost is charged by the government, and an expert fee is charged by the Professional to put up your application.<br>\r\n\r\nThe FSSAI fees for these registrations are given below:<br>\r\n\r\nFoSCoS FSSAI Basic License - Fees if annual turnover is less than 12 lakhs - 100/- per year\r\n<br>\r\nState FoSCoS FSSAI License - Fees for annual turnovers of more than 12 lakhs but less than 20 crores: 2000/- or 5000/- per year<br>\r\n\r\nCentral FoSCoS FSSAI License - Fees: 7500/- per year for annual turnover exceeding 20 crores', '85', '2021-11-16 10:06:52', '2021-11-16 18:46:16'),
(94, 'guide', '<b>Consequences for not obtaining FSSAI Registration</b><br>\r\n\r\nAll food-related enterprises must have a basic FSSAI registration. The following are the consequences of not having a valid food license:-<br>\r\n\r\nAn FFSAI logo can help your business boost the reputation of the food it sells, distributes, or stores. However, unless you have a valid registration, you will not be allowed to use the FSSAI logo on your food products.<br>\r\nIt\'s possible that getting loans for your food business could be challenging. This is because most investors, banks, and lenders favor borrowers who have a certificate over those who do not have an FSSAI license when giving loans.\r\n<br>\r\nFailure to obtain a suitable FSSAI License may result in the loss of opportunity to apply for government tenders or events, among other things.\r\n<br>\r\nYou\'re dealing with a lack of trust from your target market.\r\n<br>\r\nYou may also face a penalty of up to five lakh rupees or a six-month jail sentence if you operate a food business without a legal certificate of registration.', '85', '2021-11-16 10:06:52', '2021-11-16 18:46:16'),
(95, 'faq', '<b>Frequently asked questions:<br></b>\r\n\r\nWhat exactly is the FSSAI?<br>\r\n\r\nThe Food Safety and Standards Authority of India (FSSAI) is a self-governing organization within the Ministry of Health and Family Welfare of the Government of India that regulates and oversees food safety.\r\n<br>\r\nWhich law governs the FSSAI License?<br>\r\n\r\nFSSAI is governed by the Food Safety and Standards Act of 2006.<br>\r\n\r\nIs the FSSAI code or number alphabetical or alphanumeric?<br>\r\n\r\nThe 14-digit FSSAI code is numeric in nature, not alphanumeric or alphabetical.<br>\r\n\r\nWhen is it possible for an FSSAI Designated Officer to revoke a license?<br>\r\n\r\nIf a food business owner does not cooperate with an improvement notice, the FSSAI Designated Officer can terminate his licence after giving him the opportunity to show cause.<br>\r\n\r\nIs it possible to appeal a notice of improvement, suspension, or cancellation of a license?<br>\r\n\r\nYes, any Food Business Operator who is unhappy with their improvement notice or license suspension or cancellation can appeal to the State Commissioner of Food Safety. The Food and Safety Commissioner\'s decision will be final. Alternatively, an FBO can file a complaint with their local State/Food UT\'s Safety Appellate Tribunal/High Court to contest the notifiable condition.<br>\r\n\r\nWhat is the procedure for obtaining an FSSAI food license?<br>\r\n\r\nYou can obtain an FSSAI food license by visiting your local health department and filling out a food license application. Alternatively, go to https://foodlicensing.fssai.gov.in/ to see the FSSAI\'s official website.<br>\r\n\r\nIs a transporter\'s FSSAI license required?<br>\r\n\r\nThe cost of the basic license varies depending on the volume of business, but transporters with more than 100 cars or a turnover of more than Rs. 30 crores are obliged to get a State FSSAI license.\r\n<br>\r\nWhat is the purpose of the FSSAI?\r\n<br>\r\nAn FSSAI license is necessary for food enterprises to follow food safety and security rules and to ensure that customers receive high-quality food that meets their expectations.\r\n<br>\r\nIn the FSSAI, what is Form A?\r\n<br>\r\nA small FBO with an annual sales of less than 12 lakh must fill out Form A, which is a basic FSSAI registration.<br>\r\n\r\n10.What is the purpose of an FSSAI declaration form?\r\n<br>\r\nThe FSSAI declaration is a form that must be signed by the partner or proprietor of the business entity asking for an FSSAI license under the 2.5.1 rule of the Food Safety and Standards Act of 2006.', '85', '2021-11-16 10:06:52', '2021-11-16 18:46:16'),
(96, 'overview', '<div><b>What is shop and establishment registration?</b></div><div><br></div><div>Most companies in India, such as shops, restaurants, cafes, eateries, and so on, are now controlled and supervised by the terms of the Shop and Establishment Act, and hence must get a Shop and Establishment License. However, it is important to remember that it is governed by state legislation, and the laws and regulations differ from one state to the next. Furthermore, this act intends to provide proper and adequate working conditions for employed employees, as well as protect their earnings, holidays, and other important rights.</div><div><br></div><div>As a result, a \"Shop and Establishment License\" is a Certificate or License granted to a business, profession, or trade that is registered under the conditions of the Shop and Establishment Act. It\'s also worth noting that the Department of Labor is in charge of enforcing and enforcing all of the Act\'s rules and regulations.</div>', '86', '2021-11-16 10:12:24', '2021-11-16 18:52:45'),
(97, 'details', 'Organizations which are eligible to obtain shop and establishment registration?\r\n\r\n\r\nThe following establishments are required to obtain a Shop and Establishment License:\r\n\r\nShops and establishments run by wholesalers or retailers.\r\n\r\nService Centers are businesses that provide services to others.\r\n\r\nStorerooms, Warehouses, and Godowns are all types of storage facilities.\r\n\r\nAlso, any other places where you work.\r\n\r\nHotels, restaurants, and eateries are all available.\r\n\r\nTheatres, amusement parks, and other forms of entertainment, for example.', '86', '2021-11-16 10:12:24', '2021-11-16 18:52:45'),
(98, 'requirement', '<div><b>Documents required for shop and establishment registration</b></div><div><br></div><div>The following documents are necessary for registration under the Shop and Establishment Act:</div><div><br></div><div>Aadhar Card, PAN (Permanent Account Number) Card, Driving License, and Voter ID are examples of employer identity verification.</div><div><br></div><div>Photograph of the employer of passport size.</div><div><br></div><div>Photograph of the business or shop.</div><div><br></div><div>In the event of rented property, a copy of the Rent Agreement or Lease Deed is necessary.</div><div><br></div><div>Any Utility Bill, such as an Electricity Bill or a Water Tax Receipt for the business. However, the utility bill should not be older than two months.</div><div><br></div><div>Other documents required depending on the type of business, establishment, or business:</div><div><br></div><div>A list of the number of Trustees in the case of a Trust.</div><div><br></div><div>Association Memorandum (MOA).</div><div><br></div><div>A list of the number of members and the Chairman in the case of a Co-operative Society.</div><div><br></div><div>Partnership deed containing all pertinent information such as the firm\'s name, the names and signatures of all partners, as well as each partner\'s share proportion.</div><div><br></div><div>A copy of the RBI\'s approval is attached (Reserve Bank of India).</div><div><br></div><div>A copy of the Companies Act of 2013\'s Certificate of Incorporation (COI).</div><div><br></div><div>A certified copy of the Charity Commissioner\'s COR (Certificate of Registration).</div>', '86', '2021-11-16 10:12:24', '2021-11-16 18:52:45'),
(99, 'listicles', 'Benefits of obtaining shop and establishment registration\r\n\r\nThe following are the perks or benefits of the Shop and Establishment Registration:\r\n\r\nThe legal recognition of a shop or establishment is provided by a shop license.\r\n\r\nIt serves as a prerequisite for subsequent registrations.\r\n\r\nThis license serves as proof of business. As a result, it aids in the acquisition of extra registrations in India.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, without a Shop and Establishment License, shops are unable to open a bank account. As a result, in order to create a bank account in the name of a store or establishment, a Shop and Establishment License is required.\r\n\r\nA shop license aids in the raising of funds for a proposed company venture through venture capital or loans.', '86', '2021-11-16 10:12:24', '2021-11-16 18:52:45'),
(100, 'regs', '<p><b>Procedures involved during shop and establishment registration:</b></p><p>The following are the procedure necessary for acquiring a Shop and Establishment License:</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The Application Form can be downloaded.</p><p>The first and most important step is to obtain a registration application form from the official website of the state in where the business or establishment is located.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Fill up all the required information.</p><p>The following step is for the business owner to fill out all of the essential information. The following are examples of necessary details:</p><p>1. The Proposed Shop and Establishment\'s Name</p><p>2. Employer\'s name and contact information</p><p>3. Names and contact information for all employees on the job at the moment</p><p>4. Proof of the Registered Establishment\'s address, as well as the NOC (No-Objection Certificate) or the Rent Agreement, if the premises are rented.</p><p>5. Information about the employer\'s PAN card.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Submit the application form after filling.</p><p>Once the owner or employer has completed all of the essential facts accurately, the next step is to send the application form to either the Inspector in-charge or the Chief Inspector of the Shop and Establishment Act, together with the stipulated fee.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Verification of the Submitted Application</p><p>The application, as well as all of the supporting documents, will be vetted and scrutinized by higher authorities when it is submitted.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Issuance of a Permit</p><p>If all of the documentation presented with the applications are in compliance with the provisions of the act, the proposed shop or establishment will be awarded a certificate of registration.</p><p>Note: In big city regions, however, the procedure of acquiring registration may take 15 to 20 working days. However, the situation may differ from one state to the next.</p>', '86', '2021-11-16 10:12:24', '2021-11-17 00:56:47'),
(101, 'others', 'others', '86', '2021-11-16 10:12:24', '2021-11-16 10:12:24'),
(102, 'guide', '<div>What are the consequences of breaking the Shop and Establishment Act?</div><div><br></div><div>The Act requires the entire establishment to register as a Shop and Establishment and to abide by all of the Act\'s laws and regulations.</div><div><br></div><div>The establishment, on the other hand, would be obliged to pay the penalty if it failed to register and obey the Act\'s rules and regulations. The punishment amount would differ from state to state.</div><div><br></div><div>What are the Most Important Factors to Consider When Applying for a Shop and Establishment License?</div><div><br></div><div>The following are some of the factors to consider while applying for a Shop and Establishment Registration:</div><div><br></div><div>The appointed Inspector has the authority to visit the registered premises for verification.</div><div><br></div><div>The owner of the business is required to post the Shop and Establishment Registration certificate in a prominent location within the business.</div><div><br></div><div>Before the license expires, it must be renewed in a timely manner.</div><div><br></div><div>If the owner wishes to close his business, he must tell the inspector in writing within 15 days of the closure.</div><div><br></div><div>Regardless of the Shop and Establishment License, the owner of the prospective business must first acquire clearance from the state Department of Labor before beginning commercial operations in that state.</div>', '86', '2021-11-16 10:12:24', '2021-11-16 18:52:45');
INSERT INTO `tabs_content` (`id`, `name`, `description`, `service_id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(103, 'faq', '<div><b>Frequently asked questions:</b></div><div><br></div><div>What is the definition of a commercial establishment?</div><div><br></div><div>The term \"Commercial Establishment\" is defined by the Shop and Establishment Act to include commercial establishments such as banks, insurance companies, and trading houses; hotels, restaurants, cafes, and refreshment houses; establishments where employees do either office work or provide service; and amusement and entertainment venues such as cinema halls, theatres, and amusement parks.</div><div><br></div><div>What are the goals of the Indian Shop and Establishment License?</div><div><br></div><div>To safeguard the rights and satisfaction of workers in both the organized and unorganized sectors, including enterprises, hotels, and restaurants.</div><div><br></div><div>It also governs wages, holidays, and incentives, among other things, in order to improve employee working conditions.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>Is it necessary to register your business under the Shop and Establishment Act?</div><div><br></div><div>Yes, within 30 days of starting operations, every firm, shop, and establishment must register under the Shop and Establishment Act.</div><div><br></div><div>Explain the important elements to remember when enrolling for shop and labor certificates.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>The certificate should be prominently displayed in the store.</div><div><br></div><div>Certificate renewal before the expiration date.</div><div><br></div><div>The chief labor inspector should be notified of any changes or updates.</div><div><br></div><div>Anyone who engages in action that is prohibited by the act will face legal consequences.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>What is the duration of a Shop and Establishment License\'s validity?</div><div><br></div><div>A Shop and Establishment License is valid for one year and can be renewed once per year. Furthermore, the laws and regulations governing license issue and renewal differ from one state to the next.</div><div><br></div><div>What is the difference between a shop and a business?</div><div><br></div><div>The act of establishing; an approval or inducing; settlement; confirmation, whereas a shop is a business that sells goods or services to the general public, originally a physical place but now also a virtual location.</div><div><br></div><div>Is it necessary for all shops to register under the Shop and Establishment Act?</div><div><br></div><div>Yes, under the appropriate state shop and establishment statute, practically all stores and establishments are required to obtain a shop and establishment license.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>What are the consequences of failing to obtain such a license?</div><div><br></div><div>The consequences of failing to obtain a Shop License differ from state to state.</div><div><br></div><div>How long does it take for a business to become registered from the time it first opens?</div><div><br></div><div>A shop and establishment must be registered under the provisions of the Shop and Establishment Act within 30 days of the date of beginning.</div><div><br></div><div>10.Is it still necessary for a business to register under the Shop and Establishment Act if it has no employees?</div><div><br></div><div>Yes, the Act requires every business and shop, regardless of the number of employees, to get a Shop and Establishment License.</div><div><br></div><div>11. Do the requirements for a Shop and Establishment License differ from one state to the next?</div><div><br></div><div>Because the Shop and Establishment License is a state law, each state has its unique set of rules and requirements.</div>', '86', '2021-11-16 10:12:24', '2021-11-17 00:56:47'),
(104, 'overview', '<div><b>What is EPF Registration?</b></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem; letter-spacing: 0.0312rem;\">The Employees\' Provident Funds and Miscellaneous Provisions Act of 1952 established the Employees\' Provident Fund (EPF). It is governed by the Employees\' Provident Fund Organization (EPFO), which is one of the world\'s largest social security organizations in terms of clientele and financial transactions processed. EPF is essentially a perk granted by the company to an employee at his or her retirement.</span><br></div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem; letter-spacing: 0.0312rem;\">EPFO is the largest social security institution in the world, with a massive number of financial transactions. EPF is a retirement benefit provided to employees in the form of Provident Fund.</span><br></div>', '87', '2021-11-16 10:15:05', '2021-11-17 00:57:31'),
(105, 'details', '<div>Employer EPF Registration: Is It Necessary?</div><div><br></div><div>EPF registration is required for all establishments, defined as a factory employing 20 or more people in any industry, and any other establishment employing 20 or more people or a class of such establishments that the Central Government may specify by notification.</div><div><br></div><div>The employer must seek the registration within one month of achieving the required strength, or face fines. Even if the staff strength falls below the statutory minimum, a registered establishment remains subject to the Act.</div><div><br></div><div>After giving at least two months\' notice for compulsory registration, the Central Government may apply the regulations to any establishment with fewer than 20 employees. When the employer and the majority of employees agree that the requirements of this act should be applied to the business, they may apply to the Commissioner of the Central Provident Fund (PF).</div><div><br></div><div>The Central PF Commissioner may apply the provisions of this Act to such institution as of the date of the agreement or any later date specified in the agreement after making a notice in the Official Gazette.</div><div><br></div><div>From the start of their work, all employees will be eligible for a PF, and the employer will be responsible for deducting and paying the PF. The 12% PF contribution should be split evenly between the company and the employee. The employer contributes 12% of the employee\'s base pay. If the business employs fewer than 20 people, the PF deduction rate is 10%.</div>', '87', '2021-11-16 10:15:05', '2021-11-16 19:02:05'),
(106, 'requirement', 'What are the eligibility requirements for EPF registration?\r\n\r\nFor establishments that meet the following conditions, EPF registration is required:\r\n\r\nA factory with a staff of 20 or more employees that is engaged in a certain industry.\r\n\r\nOther establishments with 20 or more employees, or a class of similar establishments that the central government specifies in a notification on their behalf.\r\n\r\nIf an employer does not register for EPF within one month of hiring twenty employees, they may face a penalty. At the same time, if a registered organization\'s staff strength falls below the required requirement, it still falls within the Act\'s guidelines.\r\n\r\nAfter giving a two-month notice on required registration, the Central Government may impose provisions on an organization with less than 20 employees.\r\n\r\nSome businesses with fewer than 20 employees may also be required to register for the EPF, however this is done on a voluntary basis.\r\n\r\nRequired Documents for EPF Registration\r\n\r\nThe employer must attach the following documents to the \"Registration Form for EPFO\":\r\n\r\nThe Proprietor\'s/Partner\'s/PAN Director\'s Card.\r\n\r\nProof of address, such as the Electricity, Water, or Telephone Bill for the Registered Office (not older than 2 months).\r\n\r\nProprietor/Partner/Aadhar Director\'s Card\r\n\r\nAny government-issued license for the establishment, such as a shop and establishment certificate, a GST certificate, or any other government-issued license.\r\n\r\nThe Proprietor/Partner/digital Director\'s signature.\r\n\r\nEntity\'s Cancelled Cheque or Bank Statement\r\n\r\nIf applicable, there is a Hired/Rented/Leased Agreement.\r\n\r\nThe Identifier/Licensing Authority issues a License Proof.', '87', '2021-11-16 10:15:05', '2021-11-16 19:02:05'),
(107, 'listicles', 'Online EPF Registration Procedure\r\n\r\nThe employer must register the firm online. Employers can register their firm using the convenience of online registration by providing the following information:\r\n\r\nDetails on the establishment:\r\n\r\nThe details that must be supplied include the establishment\'s name, address, incorporation date, PAN, and kind of establishment.\r\n\r\nThe Factory License Number, Date of License, and Place of Issue of License must be included if the establishment is a factory.\r\n\r\nIf the business is a small or medium-sized business, MSME registration information must be submitted.\r\n\r\nIf the business is registered with Startup India, the company\'s registration information must be submitted.', '87', '2021-11-16 10:15:05', '2021-11-16 19:02:05'),
(108, 'regs', '<br>', '87', '2021-11-16 10:15:05', '2021-11-16 19:02:05'),
(109, 'others', '<p lang=\"en-US\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.28cm; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.08px; background: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: medium; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br></p>', '87', '2021-11-16 10:15:05', '2021-11-16 19:02:05'),
(110, 'guide', '<div><b>What are the advantages of joining the EPF?</b></div><div><br></div><div>Contribution of the Employer: Along with the employee, the employer contributes a percentage of the EPF fund. In addition, the company makes a contribution that includes the employee pension plan (EPS).</div><div><br></div><div>Financial Support: The provident fund provides financial assistance to employees in the event of retirement, illness, death, disability, or any other unforeseen event.</div><div><br></div><div>Employees\' carry forward PF accounts do not need to be closed if they change jobs because they can be carried forward.</div><div><br></div><div>Long-Term Plans PF funds can be utilized for long-term plans by the employee.</div><div><br></div><div>Lowers the Chances of Failure: Employee provident funds decrease a major percentage of risk, which is beneficial to both employees and their dependents. This fund will be used in the event of an emergency or other type of crisis.</div><div><br></div><div>A Single Account: After the employer completes the online PF registration, the employee is given a number that will remain the same even if the employee moves jobs. This number is good for the entire country of India. As a result, even if the employee moves to a different place in order to continue his employment, this number will remain the same.</div>', '87', '2021-11-16 10:15:05', '2021-11-16 19:02:05'),
(111, 'faq', '<div><b>Frequently asked question:</b></div><div><br></div><div><b>Why should an employer register their business with the EPFO?</b></div><div><br></div><div>After April 1, 2012, employers are only obliged to pay remittances after producing challans through the EPFO\'s employer portal. As a result, the employer must complete an online registration form. All new registrations must now be conducted online, as the offline registration procedure has been phased out.</div><div><br></div><div><b>What happens if the employer forgets the portal\'s User ID/Password?</b></div><div><br></div><div>If an employer forgets their user ID or password, they must go to the login screen and select the \"Forgot Password\" link. The establishment id, primary email id, and mobile number can all be used to reset the password.</div><div><br></div><div><b>What is not covered by the EPF when it comes to wages?</b></div><div><br></div><div>According to the Employee Provident Fund, the following entities are exempt from paying wages:</div><div><br></div><div>Allowance for Overtime (OTA)</div><div><br></div><div>Allowance for Extra Food</div><div><br></div><div>Allowance for Dearness (DA)</div><div><br></div><div>Allowance for House Rent (HRA)</div><div><br></div><div>Which employees are not covered by this plan?</div><div><br></div><div>This scheme does not apply to retired employees, employees who are going abroad for permanent residence, apprentices or interns, and so on.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><b>If an employee is paid on a daily or piece rate basis, how are contributions calculated?</b></div><div><br></div><div>The contribution is computed based on the earnings paid in a calendar month in this scenario.</div><div><br></div><div><b>What is the maximum number of authorized signatories that can be registered with EPF?</b></div><div><br></div><div>By updating its DSC on the EPFO site, an entity can register up to three authorized signatories. Such a DSC must be updated in order to check KYC documentation online and submit a PF claim online.</div><div><br></div><div><b>What should an employer do if he or she forgets his or her User ID or password?</b></div><div><br></div><div>In the event that the employer forgets his or her password, he or she can use the \'Forgot Password?\' link on the login screen. The password can be reset once the Establishment ID, primary email address, or mobile number has been supplied.</div><div><br></div><div><b>What does the acronym EPF stand for?</b></div><div><br></div><div>Employees Provident Fund</div><div><br></div><div>Employee Provident Fund (EPF) is a retirement savings scheme in which employees contribute a modest portion of their monthly earnings.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Why is it important to make an EPF contribution?</b></div><div><br></div><div>An employer\'s PF contribution will be tax-free.</div><div><br></div><div>The money, including interest, will be tax-free when withdrawn after a specified term.</div><div><br></div><div>PF rules also allow organizations to enlist themselves freely.</div><div><br></div><div><b>10.Who is qualified to participate in the EPF Plan?</b></div><div><br></div><div>This scheme applies to all firms or business premises with a workforce of more than 20 people.</div>', '87', '2021-11-16 10:15:05', '2021-11-16 19:02:05'),
(112, 'overview', '<p><b><br></b></p><p><b>What is ESI Registration?</b></p><p>Employee State Insurance, or ESI, is administered by the Employee State Insurance Corporation, an autonomous organization established by legislation under the Ministry of Labor and Employment of the Government of India.</p><p>This programme was created specifically for Indian laborers. The company provides a wide range of medical, financial, and other benefits to the employees. The ESIC requires every non-seasonal factory or business with more than 10 full - time employees (in some states, it\'s 20) and a maximum pay of Rs. 21,000/- to register.</p><p>The company is required to contribute 3.25 percent of the entire monthly salary payable to the employee under this scheme, whereas the employee is simply required to contribute 0.75 percent of his monthly wage every month of the year. Only employees earning less than Rs. 176/- per day are excused from paying their contribution.</p>', '88', '2021-11-16 10:22:09', '2021-11-17 01:01:53'),
(113, 'details', '<p><b>The Advantages of ESIC Registration:</b></p><p>Few of the advantage for signing up for this programme are listed below. Here are a few examples:</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • In the event of any certified illness lasting for a maximum of 91 days in any year, sickness benefits at a rate of 70% (in the form of salary) will be paid.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • An employee\'s and his family\'s medical benefits.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Pregnant women receive maternity benefits (paid leaves).</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • If an employee dies while on the job, 90 percent of his or her salary is paid to his or her dependents in the form of a monthly payment after the person\'s death.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • In the event of an employee\'s disability, the same rules apply.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Expenses for a funeral</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Expenses associated with medical treatment for the elderly.</p>', '88', '2021-11-16 10:22:09', '2021-11-17 01:01:53'),
(114, 'requirement', '<p><b>Required Documents for ESI Registration</b></p><p>The following are the documents needed to register for ESI:</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Obtaining a registration certificate under the Factories Act and the Shops and Establishment Act</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • MOA and AOA of the company MOA and AOA of the company Certificate of registration in the case of a company and partnership deed in the case of a partnership firm</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Employee details such as name, father\'s name, mobile number, date of birth, date of joining, salary, postal address, name of nominee, grade, identity proof such as PAN or Aadhaar, bank account number, etc. are included in the list.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Employees\' attendance registers</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The commercial establishment\'s PAN card</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Scanned copies of the company\'s licenses, such as the GST license.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • A cancelled check drawn on the company\'s bank account</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The proprietor, partner, or director\'s digital signature, as the case may be</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • A list of directors</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • List of stockholders</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Proof of address of the proprietor, partner, or board of directors, as the case may be</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The phone number and email address of the company\'s founder, partner, or director, if applicable.</p>', '88', '2021-11-16 10:22:09', '2021-11-17 01:01:53'),
(115, 'listicles', '<p><b>Process of ESI Registration</b></p><p>Previously, registration was done manually. ESIC registration is now entirely online. The steps that need to be followed for ESIC Registration are as follows:</p><p>Step 1: Go to the ESI Portal and log in.</p><p>An employer must create an account on the ESIC website.</p><p>Employers can create an account on the ESIC portal by navigating to the home page and selecting the \'Sign Up\' option under the \'Employer Login\' option.</p><p>Employers must fill up the details and submit the form after clicking the \'Sign up\' button.</p><p>Step 2: Sending a Confirmation Email</p><p>The employer will receive a confirmation email to the registered email id and cellphone number submitted at the time of sign up after submitting the form for portal sign up.</p><p>The login and password for registering as an employer and employee under the ESIC programme will be included in the email.</p><p><br></p><p>Employer Registration Form-1 (Step 3)</p><p>Then, using the username and password you received in the letter, log in to the ESIC portal. This will take you to a page where you can register as a new employer.</p><p>Select \'New Employer Registration\' from the drop-down menu. Then, from the drop-down list, choose the \'Type of Unit\' and click the \'Submit\' button. The \'Employer Registration – Form 1\' will display, which the employer must complete.</p><p>The Employer Registration Form-1 contains information on the employer\'s unit, the employer, and the employees. After the employer has filled out the entire form, he must click the \'Submit\' button.</p><p>Payment for Registration (Step 4)</p><p>Following the submission of the Employer Registration Form-1, the \'Payment of Advance Contribution\' page will appear, prompting the employer to enter the amount to be paid and the payment mechanism.</p><p>The employer will be responsible for paying the advance payment for a period of six months.</p><p>Step 5: Write a letter of registration</p><p>Following the successful payment of the six-month advance contribution, the ESIC department will send the employer a system-generated Registration Letter (C-11) with a 17-digit Registration Number.</p><p>The Registration Letter (C-11) is a legal proof of the employer\'s registration.</p>', '88', '2021-11-16 10:22:09', '2021-11-17 01:01:53'),
(116, 'regs', '<p><b>Failure to get ESI registration and returns will result in a penalty.</b></p><p>Any non-compliance by an employer, such as failing to register as an ESIC employer online or failing to comply with the ESI return filing procedure, will result in a punishment of INR 10,000/-.</p><p>What are the ESI Post-Registration Requirements?</p><p>Once an entity is covered by ESIC, it must follow the Act\'s mandatory rules, which include:</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Keeping a record of attendance</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • A full wage register for workers</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Book of inspection</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Monthly returns and challans are due by the 15th of the following month.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The register was kept to keep track of any mishaps that occurred on the premises.</p>', '88', '2021-11-16 10:22:09', '2021-11-17 01:01:53'),
(117, 'others', '<p><b>After the registration, how many returns are filed per year?</b></p><p><b><br></b>\r\nAfter completing the registration process, ESI will contact you. Returns must be filed twice a year, and the following papers must be included in the filing:\r\n    • Employees\' Attendance Register\r\n    • Register of Wages&nbsp;\r\n    • Form 6-Register\r\n    • Keep track of any accidents that have occurred on the business\'s premises.\r\n    • Returns and Challans are due every month.</p>', '88', '2021-11-16 10:22:09', '2021-11-17 01:01:53'),
(118, 'guide', '<div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>What are the ESI Post-Registration Requirements?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Once an entity is covered by ESIC, it must follow the Act\'s mandatory rules, which include:</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Keeping a record of attendance</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>A full wage register for workers</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Book of inspection</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Monthly returns and challans are due by the 15th of the following month.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>The register was kept to keep track of any mishaps that occurred on the premises.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>After the registration, how many returns are filed per year?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>After completing the registration process, ESI will contact you. Returns must be filed twice a year, and the following papers must be included in the filing:</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Employees\' Attendance Register</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Register of Wages&nbsp;</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Form 6-Register</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Keep track of any accidents that have occurred on the business\'s premises.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Returns and Challans are due every month.</b></span></font></div>', '88', '2021-11-16 10:22:09', '2021-11-16 19:04:12'),
(119, 'faq', '<p><b>Frequently asked questions:</b></p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; 1. What exactly is the ESI Scheme?</p><p>The ESI programme is a comprehensive social security scheme that is designed to socially safeguard employees in the organized sector in the event of sickness, maternity, disability, or death as a result of work-related damage.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; 2. Who is not qualified to register for ESIC?</p><p>Employees or workers earning more than Rs.21,000 per month are not covered by ESIC, while the maximum wage for a person with disabilities is Rs.25,000.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; 3. Who does not qualify for ESIC?</p><p>Employees of a covered unit who earn less than Rs. 21,000 per month will be eligible for benefits under the Scheme. Employees with a daily average remuneration of up to Rs. 176 are excused from paying ESIC.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; 4. On what kind of wage does ESIC kick in?</p><p>The ESI Act covers employees whose monthly salary are less than Rs 21,000 per month. In December 2016, the Act\'s pay ceiling was raised from Rs 15,000 per month to Rs 21,000 per month.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; 5. Is ESI registration required?</p><p>Yes, under section 2A of the Act and regulation 10-B, the employer is required to register their firm under the ESI Act within an stipulated time of 15 days on the date of applicability issued to them.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; 6. What are the basic wages used in the ESI calculation?</p><p>Wages covered by ESIC are calculated as the sum of Basic Pay + Dearness Allowances, excluding any overtime worked by the employee.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; 7. How is the scheme financed?</p><p>The ESI programme is a self-funding programme. Employer and employee contributions are principally used to support the ESI funds, which are provided monthly at a fixed percentage of salaries received.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; 8. Is the amount removed from each employee\'s pay the same?</p><p>No, the least amount to be deducted for the programme is 1.75 percent of an employee\'s salary, and the basic compensation for an employee to be enrolled is 15,000. If the employee\'s pay surpasses 15,000, the amount of deduction will be adjusted appropriately.</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; 9. Is there any interest if you pay late?</p><p>Yes, Let\'s say the employer fails to pay the contribution amount within the agreed-upon time frame. In that instance, he is obligated to pay a 12 percent annual interest rate based on the number of days he is late.</p><p>10.Is the ESIC Registration Certificate a requirement for the units?</p><p>Yes, by registering their entity under ESIC, every entity eligible under the ESIC Act will receive a certificate. ESIC\'s official website is where the applicant can apply online.</p>', '88', '2021-11-16 10:22:09', '2021-11-17 01:01:53'),
(120, 'overview', '<p><b>What is import export code registration?</b></p><p><br></p><p>In this day of strong competition, everyone wants to develop their firm beyond the home market. International business, on the other hand, isn\'t for everyone. Before going worldwide, you must adhere to a number of procedures and rules, as well as get several registrations and licenses. When importing or exporting from India, an IEC license is required. Importer-Exporter Code is one more name by which it is known.</p><p><br></p><p>Anyone wishing to open an import/export business in the country will require an Import Export Code. The DGFT is the one who is in charge of issuing it. IEC stands for International Electrotechnical Commission. It is a 10-digit designation that is valid for a lifetime. In most of the cases, the importers merchants are not able to import products without an Import Export Code, and exporters merchants can’t take use of DGFT incentives which includes export plan, etc., without an IEC.</p>', '89', '2021-11-16 10:30:37', '2021-11-17 01:04:32'),
(121, 'details', '<p><b>Situations in Which IEC Is Necessary</b></p><p><br></p><p>When an importer has to clear his cargo through customs, it is required.</p><p><br></p><p>In case, when an importer sends money abroad through a bank, the bank requires it.</p><p><br></p><p>When an exporter has to convey his shipments, the customs port requires it.</p><p><br></p><p>When an exporter receives money in foreign currency directly into his bank account, the bank requires it.</p>', '89', '2021-11-16 10:30:37', '2021-11-17 01:04:32'),
(122, 'requirement', '<p><b>Documents which are required to register for an IEC</b></p><p><br></p><p>The following documents are needed for IEC Code Registration:</p><p><br></p><p>A copy of a person\'s PAN card, a firm\'s PAN card, or a company\'s PAN card. Either of them will work.</p><p><br></p><p>Voter id, Aadhar card, or passport copy of an individual are needed.</p><p><br></p><p>Individuals, organizations, and firms can cancel cheque copies of existing bank accounts.</p><p><br></p><p>Copy of the firm or a copy of the rent agreement or a copy of the electric bill should be submitted.</p><p><br></p><p>A self-addressed envelope for the IEC certificate\'s registered mail delivery.</p><p><br></p><p>For address verification, you need have a scanned copy of the rental/lease deed, the sale deed, and the electricity/phone bill.</p><p><br></p><p>If an applicant is a Non-Resident Indian (NRI) or there is a Non-Resident stake in the company/firm, you must send a scanned copy of the RBI permission letter.</p><p><br></p><p>You should have a scanned copy of a \'Cancelled Cheque\' with the Entity\'s or Individual\'s name pre-printed on it OR he should have a \'Bankers Certificate\' in the approved format.</p><p><br></p><p>In case of online payment of government fees of Rs. 500/-, you must have a \'Debit/Credit card or Net Banking account.</p>', '89', '2021-11-16 10:30:37', '2021-11-17 01:04:32'),
(123, 'listicles', '<p><b>IEC Registration Benefits&nbsp;</b></p><p><br></p><p>Expansion of the company IEC can assist you in expanding your business by bringing your services or products to a global market.</p><p><br></p><p>Taking Advantage of a Variety of Advantages.</p><p><br></p><p>Enterprises may be eligible for incentives from the DGFT, Export Promotion Council, Customs, and many others based on their IEC registration for imports and exports.</p><p><br></p><p>There will be no filing of returns.</p><p><br></p><p>There are no returns that must be filed with the IEC. Once it has been assigned, there is no need to follow any procedures in order to keep it valid. In case of DGFT for export transactions, there is no need to file any returns.</p><p><br></p><p>Processing is simple.</p><p><br></p><p>Obtaining an IEC code from the DGFT within 10 to 15 days of filing an application is extremely simple. To receive an IEC code, there is no need to show proof of any export or import.</p><p><br></p><p>There is no requirement for renewal.</p><p><br></p><p>IEC codes do not need to be renewed because they are valid for the life of the entity. An entity can use it to apply to all export and import transactions once it has obtained it.</p>', '89', '2021-11-16 10:30:37', '2021-11-17 01:04:32'),
(124, 'regs', '<p><b>When is it necessary to register for an Import Export Code?</b></p><p><br></p><p>The following situations necessitate IEC registration:</p><p><br></p><p>Importer\'s shipments must be cleared by customs authorities.</p><p><br></p><p>This code is required when sending money abroad through a licensed bank.</p><p><br></p><p>Exporting shipments to other countries.</p><p><br></p><p>This code is required by the bank when the exporter receives inward remittance.</p><p><br></p><p>This code is necessary for Food Licensing and FSSAI registration.</p><p><br></p><p>This code is necessary for APEDA registration.</p><p><br></p><p>This number is essential if the exporter receives any type of subsidy.</p><p><br></p><p>IEC (Import/Export Code) Registration Procedures</p><p><br></p><p>Step 1: Fill out the application form</p><p><br></p><p>Firstly, fill out and submit an application form in the guided format (Aayaat Niryaat Form ANF-2A) to the appropriate DGFT Regional office.</p><p><br></p><p>Step 2: Gathering Documents</p><p><br></p><p>Second, you must gather the necessary identification and legal entity papers, as well as an address proof that includes your bank account details and an ANF2A certificate.</p><p><br></p><p>Step 3: Submitting Your Application</p><p><br></p><p>You\'ll need to present your application to DGFT via Digital Signature Certificate and pay the IEC Registration fee after you\'ve completed it.</p><p><br></p><p>Step 4: International Electrotechnical Commission (IEC) Code</p><p><br></p><p>Finally, if your application is approved, you will get a soft copy of the IEC Code from the government.</p><p><br></p>', '89', '2021-11-16 10:30:37', '2021-11-17 01:04:32'),
(125, 'others', '<div><b>When is it necessary to register with the IEC?</b></div><div><br></div><div>Importing and exporting commodities necessitates the completion of an IEC registration. It communicates the vendor code information to the port where the products or administrations are imported or exported. The illegal transportation of commodities is restricted, and as a result, the IEC aids in reducing it, as it is almost impossible to obtain an import export code without providing the whole details on the items being imported or exchanged.</div><div><br></div><div>Only if you have an IEC number will customs clear your package as an importer.</div><div><br></div><div>To send money internationally, a bank must be registered with the IEC.</div><div><br></div><div>An exporter must register with the IEC at the customs port in order for his cargo to clear.</div>', '89', '2021-11-16 10:30:37', '2021-11-17 01:04:32'),
(126, 'guide', '<p><b>When an Export Import Code (EIC) isn\'t Required</b></p><p><br></p><p>IEC is not necessary for all GST-registered traders, according to the government\'s most recent circular. The trader\'s PAN will be considered as a new IEC code for import and export operations in all of these cases. An Import Export Code (IEC) is not necessary if the products being exported or imported are for personal use and not for commercial purposes. Notified Charitable Institutions do not need an Import Export Code for export/import conducted by Government of India Departments and Ministries.</p>', '89', '2021-11-16 10:30:37', '2021-11-17 01:04:32'),
(127, 'faq', '<p><b>Frequently asked questions:</b></p><p><br></p><p>Is there a way to use electronic signatures for the IEC?</p><p><br></p><p>Yes, electronic signatures can be used for the IEC. Sole proprietors and other entities other than sole proprietors can utilize E-Signature for Aadhaar virtual ID. Validation is also possible using this system.</p><p><br></p><p>Is it feasible to make changes to an IEC application?</p><p><br></p><p>Yes, you can make changes to an existing IEC application. The applicant should click to the Manage Services option under Service Registration. After that, proceed to the validate tab, where you\'ll get information about the DSC. The applicant can make changes by clicking here.</p><p><br></p><p>Is the PAN number taken into account for the IEC?</p><p><br></p><p>Yes, after the introduction of the GST, the IEC would evaluate the name number.</p><p><br></p><p>What are the ramifications of failing to obtain an IEC (Import Export Code) certification?</p><p><br></p><p>The following are the ramifications of failing to take the IEC:</p><p><br></p><p>There can be no export or import activities.</p><p><br></p><p>There can be no remittance.</p><p><br></p><p>No remittances can be received by foreign banks.</p><p><br></p><p>Is it possible to link the IEC number to the IEC number?</p><p><br></p><p>Yes, the applicant can link the IEC number once it has been given. This procedure must be completed online via the DGFT website.</p><p><br></p><p>Is it possible for a person to apply for an import/export code?</p><p><br></p><p>Yes, anyone can apply for the import export code. This application, however, must be submitted as a sole proprietorship.</p><p><br></p><p>Is it possible to obtain an IEC code without obtaining a digital signature certificate?</p><p><br></p><p>Yes, even without a DSC, an IEC code can be obtained.</p><p><br></p><p>How many IECs can one person apply for?</p><p><br></p><p>There is a limit of one IEC per person or business. If the operations are carried out by distinct entities, however, different IECs must be created for each business separately.</p><p><br></p><p>Is there anything else I need to do after I submit the IEC code?</p><p><br></p><p>There is no extra compliance necessary under the authority for anyone who has applied for the IEC.</p><p><br></p><p>10.What exactly do you mean when you say \"bank details validation\"?</p><p><br></p><p>(a) Bank details will be checked using \'PFMS,\' and the results will be available the following day. (c) The risk will be marked in RMS, and the IEC will be sent to the user right away. (c) If the bank details validation is successful, the ‘RMS\' flag will be removed. (c) If it fails, the \'RMS\' Flag will be disabled.</p><p><br></p><p>11.Why is IEC registration on the DGFT website required?</p><p><br></p><p>You can create your own user profile with it. It allows you to apply for IEC, link IEC, and view IEC dashboard all in one place, as well as simply apply for and track applications. You can also receive notifications via the dashboard, mobile device, or email.</p>', '89', '2021-11-16 10:30:37', '2021-11-17 01:04:32'),
(128, 'overview', '<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 21.3333px; letter-spacing: normal;\">ISO (International Organization for Standardization) is an independent international organization that develops international standards such as ISO 9001 and ISO 14001, however it is not involved in ISO certification and does not issue ISO certificates, as its name implies. The ISO certification procedure is carried out in India by external certification bodies.</span>', '90', '2021-11-16 10:52:40', '2021-11-16 19:15:24'),
(129, 'details', '<div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>Benefits of ISO Registration</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>International credibility: ISO certification is critical in establishing an organization\'s credibility in international business.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>Customer Satisfaction: ISO standards are designed to help businesses provide better service to their consumers while also increasing customer satisfaction.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>Government Tenders: ISO Certification is essential to bid on government tenders.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>Organizational Functional Efficiency: Obtaining ISO Certification improves the functional efficiency of organizations. SOPs (Standard Operating Procedures) and work instructions can be developed with the help of the ISO Certification Agency. An organization\'s resources are better managed when ISO is implemented.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>Product Quality: Obtaining ISO Certification ensures that product quality meets international standards, lowering the chance of product order rejections caused by defective products.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>Marketability: ISO certification enhances a company\'s credibility and directly aids in marketing.</b></span></font></div>', '90', '2021-11-16 10:52:40', '2021-11-16 19:15:24'),
(130, 'requirement', '<div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>What are the Documents needed for ISO Certification?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>The first stage in the documentation process is to determine the type of ISO certification the company requires. The following is a list of the essential documents for ISO Registration.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>The applicant\'s identity and residence is a must thing that should be verified, as well as a copy of their PAN and Aadhar cards.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Size of a Passport In the event of owned property, a copy of the sale deed is required. Photograph of the Utility Bill or Electricity Bill</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>A Rent Agreement is needed for the businesses which are located in a rented premises.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>In case of the company a Certificate of Incorporation, as well as a MOA and AOA, are necessary.</b></span></font></div>', '90', '2021-11-16 10:52:40', '2021-11-16 19:15:24');
INSERT INTO `tabs_content` (`id`, `name`, `description`, `service_id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(131, 'listicles', '<div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>Choosing an ISO Certification Type</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>First and foremost, the entrepreneur must determine the type of ISO certification that is required for his or her company. There are a variety of ISO certifications available, including the ones listed below:</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>OHSAS 18001 – It takes into account the Occupational Health and Safety Management System&nbsp;</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>ISO 37001 – Anti-bribery Management Systems&nbsp;</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>ISO 9001:2008 – Quality Management System</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>ISO 31000 – Risk Management&nbsp;</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>ISO 27001 – It takes into account the Information and Security Management System&nbsp;</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"