tyle=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>Country codes (ISO 3166)</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>Date and time format ISO 8601</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>ISO 20121 – Sustainable events</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: normal;\"><b>SO/IEC 27001 – Information security management</b></span></font></div>', '90', '2021-11-16 10:52:40', '2021-11-16 19:15:24'),
(132, 'regs', '<div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Choosing an ISO Certification Organization (ISO Registrar)</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>As previously indicated, ISO does not certify businesses. External certifying agencies are responsible for this. As a result, it is necessary to recognize a reputable certification authority. When choosing a certification body, the entrepreneur must consider the following factors.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Examine a number of certification organizations.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Check to see if the certifying organization follows the CASCO standards.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Check to see if the certification organization is accredited.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Note that accreditation is not required; nonetheless, companies must meet the requirements of the ISO accreditation agencies.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>India\'s ISO Certification Process</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>The following is a step-by-step guide to gaining ISO certification in India:</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Fill out an application</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>After selecting an ISO standard and an ISO certification body, the entrepreneur or application must submit an application in the acceptable manner (depends on the ISO registrar). Liability issues, confidentiality, and access rights should all be addressed in the application, as well as the rights and obligations of the entrepreneur and certifying body parties.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Registrar\'s Review of Documents</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>All quality manuals and papers pertaining to the organization\'s various policies and procedures will be reviewed by the ISO certification authority. Examining previous work will assist the ISO registrar in identifying any potential gaps in the ISO standards\' requirements.</b></span></font></div>', '90', '2021-11-16 10:52:40', '2021-11-16 19:15:24'),
(133, 'others', '<div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b>Pre-assessment Needs Determination</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b>The Pre-assessment is an initial inspection of an organization\'s Quality Management System to detect any serious flaws or omissions in the system, and the registrar will provide the organization an opportunity to fix the problems before the normal registration assessment.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b>Make a plan of action.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b>The applicant or entrepreneur must prepare an action plan to close current gaps in the company after receiving information from the ISO registrar. The action plan should include a list of the actions that must be completed in order to meet the Quality Management System\'s requirements.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b>Note: In order to create a quality management system, the entrepreneur may need to provide training to personnel. Make sure that all of the company\'s personnel are aware of the ISO requirements for job efficiency and quality.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b>Inspection or audit on-site</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b>To audit the modifications made in the organization, the ISO registrar will undertake a physical onsite inspection.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b>If the registrar discovers anything that does not comply with the ISO standards during the audit, the registrar decides the severity and issues findings. Nonconformities are audit results that are classified into two categories based on their severity.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b>A minor non-conformance is one that involves small breaches of procedures or modest system failures to fulfil ISO requirements.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b>A major non-conformance is one in which nonconforming items are likely to reach customers or where the quality system has broken down, resulting in an inefficient system in satisfying the standards\' criteria.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b>Final inspection</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b>The registration cannot proceed until the Registrar has closed and verified any serious nonconformities. This normally entails a re-audit of the impacted regions, as well as the costs connected with it.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b>Note that minor nonconformities necessitate the creation of a remedial action plan, which will be completed at the initial surveillance.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b>Obtain an ISO Certificate</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b>After all nonconformities have been remedied and all findings have been updated in the ISO audit report, the registrar will award ISO certification.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b>Audits of Surveillance</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 21.3333px;\"><b>The purpose of the surveillance audit will be to guarantee that the organization is adhering to ISO quality standards. It would be performed on a regular basis.</b></span></font></div>', '90', '2021-11-16 10:52:40', '2021-11-16 19:15:24'),
(134, 'guide', '<div>There is a cost associated with the ISO Certification Process.</div><div><br></div><div>The cost of ISO certification is not fixed and varies from one company to the next. The ISO certification agency assesses the cost of ISO certification for each organization separately, taking into account several factors such as:</div><div><br></div><div>Employees\' number</div><div><br></div><div>Processes Performed</div><div><br></div><div>The management system\'s complexity</div><div><br></div><div>The total number of shifts worked, for example.</div><div><br></div><div>The ISO Certification Process takes time.</div><div><br></div><div>The time it takes to complete the entire ISO certification procedure varies from company to company. After examining the size of the organization, the ISO certification agency can provide a reasonable estimate. The following is an estimate of how long the ISO certification procedure will take:</div><div><br></div><div>6–8 months for small businesses</div><div><br></div><div>8-12 months for medium-sized businesses</div><div><br></div><div>12-15 months for a large organization</div>', '90', '2021-11-16 10:52:40', '2021-11-16 19:15:24'),
(135, 'faq', '<div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Frequently asked questions:</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Is there a certificate available at the pre-audit stage?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>No, there is no certificate during the pre-audit stage. The auditor will focus entirely on your company\'s business system and procedures in order to make recommendations on how to improve ISO compliance.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Is it possible for me to select any ISO accreditation?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>No, not all ISO certifications are legitimate. It is necessary that you select the appropriate ones.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Is it necessary for me to renew my ISO certificate?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Not much, however auditors undertake surprise checks now and then to determine if your company\'s standards and procedures meet the ISO certification.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Is ISO certification equivalent to a permit or a license?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>ISO accreditation is only for standards and has no bearing on permits or licenses. Even if you have an ISO certification, you will still require government and authority authorization, licenses, and licenses to conduct your business.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>What are some of the advantages of ISO certification?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>The International standard supports its own benefits within each industry; however, the certifications\' common benefits include increased market potential, compliance with procurement tenders, improved efficiency and cost savings, a higher level of customer service and thus satisfaction, and increased staff morale and motivation. Customers will know you are serious about their needs if you have a recgnised management standard.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>How long does ISO certification last?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>In India, the ISO certificate is valid for only three years. You can reapply for ISO accreditation, but the procedure stays the same. The reassessment process comprises document verification and assessments of quality management systems, both of which must be maintained in the long run. Recertification can be applied for before the certificate expires, that is, before the third year has passed.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>During the time that the ISO certificate is valid, the ISO authority conducts an annual evaluation of the system and closely monitors it.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>When it comes to ISO certification and accreditation, what\'s the difference?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>In simple terms, accreditation is a type of certification; however, accreditation should not be confused with certification or registration.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Why is ISO 9001 a requirement?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>Although ISO 9001 is not a legal obligation, it may be imposed by a client. For example, to be eligible for tenders and work, you may need to acquire ISO 9001 certification.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>What exactly is an ISO audit?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>ISO auditing is a basic technique for ensuring that an organization\'s quality process system is in compliance with the requirements. Once you\'ve obtained ISO certification, you\'ll need to conduct an annual ISO audit.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>10.Is it possible to transfer ISO certification?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>An ISO certification can be transferable; however the present certificate must first be accredited by an IAF or registrar.</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>11.What is ISO 27001?</b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b><br></b></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><b>ISO 27001 is a standard for a company\'s information security management system that defines best practices.</b></span></font></div>', '90', '2021-11-16 10:52:40', '2021-11-16 19:15:24'),
(136, 'overview', '<div><b>What is PSARA License?</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>Various individuals are heading out to start their own firms or develop their own establishments in the world we live in today. The rapid growth of small firms in the commercial sector has resulted in an increased requirement for security and safety.</div><div>Security agencies are companies that specialize in training and delivering security services. Today, a plethora of private security firms have sprung up to meet the security demands of both individuals and corporations. The Private Security Firms (Regulation) Act, 2005 regulates all operations and activities of the numerous private security agencies in India (PSARA).</div>', '91', '2021-11-16 19:21:20', '2021-11-16 19:21:20'),
(137, 'details', '<div><b>The Advantages of Obtaining a PSARA License</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>The public\'s concern for security grows in tandem with the rise in crime, necessitating the usage of private security services. Solitary or anti-national elements are forming alliances in order to defend themselves. The government has developed legislation such as the Private Security Agencies Regulation Act to assist such organizations, which rewards, organizes, and monitors their operations.</div><div>Under the wording of this legislation, no individual or private security agency is permitted to operate a business providing protection services to other private business enterprises, individuals, or property. As a result, the government acts as a conduit for granting licenses to such organizations while also verifying that they follow the Act\'s criteria.</div><div>Under the wording of this legislation, no individual or private security agency is permitted to operate a business providing protection services to other private business enterprises, individuals, or property.&nbsp;</div><div>Below are few more advantages:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Gives the training company more influence.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Increases the number of consumers</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Denial of rights and services should be avoided.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Assists in acquiring potential customers\' trust.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Increases the agency\'s credibility</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Ensures the organization\'s smooth operation</div>', '91', '2021-11-16 19:21:20', '2021-11-16 19:21:20'),
(138, 'requirement', '<div><span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.4992px; font-weight: bolder;\">Documents Required to Apply for a PSARA License</span><br></div><div><br class=\"Apple-interchange-newline\"><b></b></div><div>The following certificates of registration are available:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • PAN</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • GSTIN Registration for Provident Funds</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • ESIC is an acronym for \"European Social Insurance (Employees State Insurance Corporation) Registration</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Under the Shops and Commercial Establishments Act, you must register your business. Under the Labor Act, you must register your business.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Proof of the directors\' and workers\' identities</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Copies of the Directors\' Income Tax Returns</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Two passport-size photographs of the promoters, as well as their PANs are required.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Affidavit of Agency Office Proof of Address as required by Section 7 (2) of PSARA, 2005</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Affidavit of security training</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Certificate of Incorporation (Certificate of Incorporation)</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Memorandum of Understanding (MOU) with the training institute has been signed.</div>', '91', '2021-11-16 19:21:20', '2021-11-16 19:21:20'),
(139, 'listicles', '<div><b>PSARA\'s Eligibility Criteria</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>When it comes to the sort of company entity,</div><div>The following entities are eligible to register and get a PSARA license under the PSARA, 2005:</div><div>Sole Proprietorship, One Person Company, Partnership Firm, LLP, Association of Persons, and Private Limited Company are all examples of limited liability companies.</div><div>In terms of the Director/Principal Officer\'s job,</div><div>The qualification to be a Director/Principal Officer is not open to everyone. To be eligible for the same, you must meet the following requirements: -</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Citizenship in India is required.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Minimum age should be 18 years old to apply.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Must have sufficient financial resources to cover business expenses.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • There must be no convictions against him whatsoever.</div><div>In terms of a Security Guard\'s job description,</div><div>You can acquire a job as a security guard if you check the following boxes:-</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Citizenship in India is required.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • You must be between the ages of 18 and 65 in order to participate.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Prior experience is required.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • In any circumstances, must not be fired from any government position.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Must have all of the desired physical characteristics.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • It is necessary to convey assurance about the individual\'s character.</div>', '91', '2021-11-16 19:21:20', '2021-11-16 19:21:20'),
(140, 'regs', '<div><b>How to Apply for a PSARA License</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>Organize all of the required documentation.</div><div>The relevant documents for the application must be collected and sorted in order to ensure that the application is processed quickly and smoothly, which will speed up the process of acquiring the license.</div><div>The documentation pertaining to the various registrations, as well as the details of the promoters and directors, must be clear and legible to avoid any disputes. After obtaining the necessary documents, you can submit your application through the online portal. Because the e-signing capability is available, the entire process can be completed on the internet portal itself.</div><div>A Memorandum of Understanding (MOU) should be signed with a training organization.</div><div>A list of qualified training institutes will be shown on the home page of https://psara.gov.in. To be able to provide training to its candidates, the application must sign into an MoU with a training institute.</div><div>An agency that offers training will appeal to more people and will be able to boast about its high-quality staff. When it comes to the agency\'s training standards, ex-servicemen are permitted certain latitude and exemptions.</div><div>Application submission</div><div>The applicant must submit a PSARA License application (Form-I) to the relevant state government after completing all of the preceding procedures. The applicant should also provide Form-II, which will be used to verify the applicant\'s antecedents. Along with Form-I, an affidavit in Form-III is required.</div><div>The police conduct the verification.</div><div>The next step includes the police verification. This verification will take place when the Form-I has been submitted. If the agency is a partnership or a corporation, the directors will be required to go through the police verification process as well.</div><div>PSARA License is granted</div><div>If the application is supported by a No Objection Certificate (NOC) from the police following verification, the authority will review it and either issue or refuse the PSARA License in Form-IV, depending on the circumstances.</div><div>How long does it take to get a PSARA license?</div><div>The length of time it takes to receive a PSARA license is totally dependent on the state government in question and how quickly it processes applications. A 60-day time window from the date of receipt is appropriate for granting an application.</div><div>Supervisors are appointed.</div><div>In order to comply with the provisions of the PSARA, 2005, the applicant must pick supervisors. The supervisors are in charge of overseeing and directing the agency\'s activities in respect to the security guards\' duties. Supervisory positions must be filled by those with at least three years of experience in the army or navy.</div>', '91', '2021-11-16 19:21:20', '2021-11-16 19:21:20'),
(141, 'others', '<div><b>PSARA License Validity and Renewal</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>A PSARA License is only valid for five years after it is issued. The validity of this license is one year in Uttarakhand, Madhya Pradesh, and Chhattisgarh. The license can be simply renewed 90 days before it expires by filing a renewal application and paying the renewal price.</div>', '91', '2021-11-16 19:21:20', '2021-11-16 19:21:20'),
(142, 'guide', '<div><b>PSARA Requirements</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>The Private Security Agencies Regulation Act (PSARA) of 2005 mandates that the Private Security Agency (PSA) follow certain guidelines:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Supervisors should be hired by a private security firm to oversee the work of the company\'s guards.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Security guards will be trained by Private Security Agencies (PSA).</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • For the role of supervisor, ex-defense candidates with three years of experience would be given precedence.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • PSA security workers must adhere to the company\'s uniform policy.</div>', '91', '2021-11-16 19:21:20', '2021-11-16 19:21:20'),
(143, 'faq', '<div><b>Frequently asked questions:</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 1 What Is The PSARA License’s Validity?&nbsp;</div><div>In most states, the license to hire or provide private security guards issued under The Private Security Agencies (Regulation) Act, 2005 is valid for five years. In states like Chhattisgarh and Uttarakhand, however, it is only valid for a year. The renewal of the license can be done up to 90 days before it expires.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 2 Is the process for obtaining a PSARA license different in each state?&nbsp;</div><div>Yes, the Private Security Agencies (Regulation) Act, 2005, was passed by the Indian Parliament as the key law regulating the private security industry. However, it states that each state or union territory must nominate a regulating authority and establish regulations and procedures for applying for a PSARA license.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 3 Who is ineligible to apply for the PSARA license?</div><div>Anyone who is disqualified under section 6 of the PSARA Act of 2005 is ineligible to apply for a PSARA License.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 4 What is the PSARA License Fee Structure?</div><div>A cost of Rs 5000 would be levied if an individual just desires a PSARA license for one district. However, if he/she wants a license for five districts or the entire state, the fees will be Rs 10000 and Rs 25000, respectively (except in Karnataka, where the fee would be Rs 50000).</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 5 When is the best time to apply for a PSARA license renewal?</div><div>Renewal of a PSARA license must be requested at least 90 days prior to the license\'s expiration date.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 6 Who are the people who can apply for a PSARA licensee?</div><div>Individuals, one-person businesses, partnership firms, limited liability partnerships, and private limited companies are all qualified to apply for a PSARA license.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 7 Is it necessary for me to seek for a separate PSARA license in order to operate my agency in other states?</div><div>Yes, if a business owner wants to operate in more than one state, he or she must apply for a separate PSARA license. Furthermore, the process for obtaining a PSARA license varies per state.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 8 Is it possible for a foreign company to seek for a PSARA license?</div><div>No, a foreign corporation cannot seek for a PSARA license in India.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 9 When does the PSARA license expire and can it be renewed?</div><div>With the exception of Chhattisgarh and Uttarakhand, the PSARA License is valid for five years from the date of enrollment in most states. The states of Chhattisgarh and Uttarakhand have agreed to provide a one-year grant.</div><div>PSARA License renewal should be possible starting 90 days before the expiration date.</div><div>10.Who is in charge of issuing PSARA licenses?</div><div>PSARA permits are issued solely by state officials. PSARA licences are required in each state.</div>', '91', '2021-11-16 19:21:20', '2021-11-16 19:21:20'),
(144, 'overview', '<div><b>What is drug license?</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>Every firm that deals with medications and pharmaceuticals needs a drug license. This license would include the essential needs for a pharmaceutical company to operate on a daily basis. The government has established strict regulations for the manufacture and distribution of medications and pharmaceuticals. The provisions of the Drugs and Cosmetics Act, 1940 must be followed by any pharmaceutical dealing with the distribution of pharmaceuticals.</div><div>Under the requirements of the aforesaid statute, several types of medications and pharmaceuticals are regulated. Homeopathy, allopathy, Ayurveda, and Unani medications are examples of these types of drugs. Under the 1940 Pharmaceuticals and Cosmetics Act, any pharmaceutical supplying drugs without a formal license would be accountable. Furthermore, the Indian Penal Code, 1860, would impose severe punishments for this offence.</div>', '92', '2021-11-16 23:07:54', '2021-11-16 23:07:54'),
(145, 'details', '<div><div style=\"\"><b>Licensing of Drugs in Various Forms</b></div><div style=\"\"><b><br></b></div><div style=\"\">There are various types of drug licenses that can be given depending on the applicant\'s needs. The following are the several types of drug licenses that are available:</div><div style=\"\">Import Drug License: This type of license is typically used to bring medications in from foreign nations.</div><div style=\"\">Multi Drug License- This type of license is typically awarded to pharmaceutical companies with pharmacies in multiple states and localities. Medplus is a well-known example of this type of licensing.</div><div style=\"\">Manufacturing License- This is a license that is frequently given to large pharmaceutical companies. This type of license allows for the production of any type of medicine. This type of license can be used to manufacture both allopathic and ayurvedic medications.</div><div style=\"\">This license is typically provided for the sale of drugs in pharmacies and other retail establishments. Stores selling medications, restricted pharmaceuticals, and other items are granted this license</div></div><div><b>Advantages of a Drug License</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>The pharmacy can benefit from obtaining a drug license in the following ways:&nbsp;</div><div>Compliance with the Law- All pharmacies with a drug license are bound by the terms of the 1940 Drugs and Cosmetics Act. Apart from that, pharmacists would not be subject to any penalties for non-compliance issues.</div><div>Public perception- Pharmacies with a drug license would have a better public perception.</div><div><br></div>', '92', '2021-11-16 23:07:54', '2021-11-16 23:07:54'),
(146, 'requirement', '<div><b>Drug License Eligibility Criteria (Online Drug License)</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>For a drug license, the applicant must meet the following requirements:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • First and foremost, the applicant must have enough facilities to distribute and sell pharmaceutical products. The applicant must be able to apply for a drug license from an independent retailer. A retail or whole-sale drug license is required for such an application. The premises must be at least 10 square meters if the license is issued under Form 20 or Form 21. The premises must be at least 15 square meters if the licensing application is in Form 20-B or Form 21-B.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Storage Facilities- In order to operate, all pharmacies and drug stores must have sufficient storage facilities. Because certain pharmaceuticals and substances must be stored at low temperatures, such regulations are required. As a result, the applicant must guarantee that adequate storage facilities are available on site.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Technical Staff- All pharmacy employees must meet specific educational and technical standards. For example, all individuals must hold a bachelor\'s degree in pharmacy (B.Pharm). Aside from that, any pharmacy must have someone with one to four years of experience. When it comes to having a retail business vs a wholesale firm, the standards are different.</div>', '92', '2021-11-16 23:07:54', '2021-11-16 23:07:54');
INSERT INTO `tabs_content` (`id`, `name`, `description`, `service_id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(147, 'listicles', '<div><b>Documents for obtaining a drug license</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Documents for forming a corporation and establishing a constitution- If the applicant is a corporation, the certificate of organization, as well as other documents such as the memorandum of association and articles of incorporation, must be given. If the entity is a partnership, the partnership documentation must be given as well. The partnership document will be included in this.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Proof of the Director\'s or Shareholder\'s or Applicant\'s identity.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Utility bills, power bills, water bills, and property paperwork are examples of premises documentation.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The Pharmaceutical Outlet\'s Site Plan and Architecture Plan</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • A copy of the Board Resolution pertaining to the License is attached.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Proof of Challan and a copy of the Pharmacy Deposit Fee</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Evidence demonstrating the availability of a storage facility as well as cold storage facilities.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The evidence shows that neither the partner nor the company\'s director has been convicted.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The pharmacist\'s educational qualifications and experience.</div><div>Forms for obtaining a drug license are required.</div><div>The candidate for a drug license is required to complete out appropriate application forms.</div><div>The following are the forms that must be completed and submitted by the applicant:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • This form is used to sell, distribute, and store drugs for distribution. Schedule X medications are required to be displayed or sold in accordance with the Drugs and Cosmetics Act of 1940.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Form 19A is an application for a restricted license to sell medicines and drugs that is being granted or renewed.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • This type of license would apply to retailers who do not employ the services of a qualified worker.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Form 19C- This application is for a license to sell, stock, or distribute medicines listed in Schedule X of the Act, or for a renewal of a license to sell, stock, or distribute medicines listed in Schedule X of the Act.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Form 20B is an application for the wholesale sale or distribution of drugs.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Form 21C-Application for a specific renewal of a wholesale license for the sale or distribution of pharmaceuticals.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Form 24- Application for granting or renewing a license for specific medications, or for manufacturing, selling, or distributing drugs other than those listed in Schedule X, Schedule C, or Schedule C1.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • This form would contain an application for a loan license in the form of Form 24A. The purpose of this license is to award or renew a lending license for medicines and pharmaceutical products.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Form 24B-Application form for repackaging medications and other types of drugs, save those included in Schedule X, Schedule C, or Schedule C1 of the Drugs and Cosmetics Act, 1940.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Form 24C is a request for a renewal of a license to make and distribute homoeopathic remedies.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Form 24F-Application for renewal of a license for the sale and manufacture of medications listed in Schedule X, but not for the manufacture and sale of drugs listed in Schedules C and C1.</div>', '92', '2021-11-16 23:07:54', '2021-11-16 23:07:54'),
(148, 'regs', '<div><b>In India, the procedure for obtaining a drug license is as follows:</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>For this type of license in India, the following procedures must be followed:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Fill out an online application for the appropriate state drug license- The applicant must first complete an online application for the appropriate state drug license. The requirements for obtaining a drug license change from one state to the next. As a result, the applicant must ensure that the drug licensing criteria are in line with the state standards.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Offer Updated Documents and Upload Them- The applicant must provide updated documents and upload them online in the second phase. Such documents must comply with the authority\'s standards.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Pay the Fees- The next step is for the applicant to pay the drug licensing fees. This must be done via the internet.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Verification- After submitting an application for a license, it will be verified. The application will be checked by the concerned authority. The premises of the retail or wholesale shop would be inspected by an inspector. The inspector will approve the premises if all of the requirements match the requirements.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The authority will then grant the drug license as the final stage.</div>', '92', '2021-11-16 23:07:54', '2021-11-16 23:07:54'),
(149, 'others', 'others&nbsp;', '92', '2021-11-16 23:07:54', '2021-11-16 23:07:54'),
(150, 'guide', 'guide&nbsp;', '92', '2021-11-16 23:07:54', '2021-11-16 23:07:54'),
(151, 'faq', '<div><b>Frequently asked questions:</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 1 What kind of establishments will be granted a drug license?</div><div>Typically, drug licenses are only issued to a shop or facility in a commercial setting.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 2 What are the requirements for a registered pharma firm to keep accounts?</div><div>The licensing body may specify the way in which the books of accounts, registers, forms, and other papers must be kept at the time the license is issued. It is the license holder\'s responsibility to notify the licensing authority of any changes or modifications to its business.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 3 Is it true that different licenses are required for each drug-related operation?</div><div>Yes, any unit functioning in any area of India requires a drug license. For example, if a pharma company has operations in two states, it must obtain licenses for both of them.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 4 What are the different types of licenses available?</div><div>The following are the many types of licenses that are available:</div><div>Export and Import Licenses, Manufacturing Licenses, Sales Licenses, and Loan Licenses and Licensure for multiple drugs.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 5 What is the average time it takes to obtain a drug license?</div><div>After the application submits the required information for the drug license, the applicant will receive the license within one month.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 6 Is it legal to bring pharmaceuticals into India?</div><div>All activities linked to the manufacture, distribution, and sale of medications must be controlled under the Drugs and Cosmetics Act of 1940. Only after obtaining a specific import license is it feasible to bring medicines into the country.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 7 Is it feasible to get your drug license renewed?</div><div>The drug license can be renewed, and it is possible to do so. To renew a drug license, the applicant must provide the required documentation. These documents must be posted to the website where the shop or location is located. Following this, the authorities will grant a license for a specific time period.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 8 What distinguishes a drug license from others?</div><div>The following are the characteristics of a drug license:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • A drug license is required for any firm that sells pharmaceuticals, medicines, or cosmetics.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The license will be issued for a commercial establishment.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The pharmaceutical and cosmetics industries must adhere to all legal and regulatory requirements and restrictions.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The license must be displayed in the place of business at all times.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 9 What is the purpose of a drug license?</div><div>To carry out the process of manufacturing, distributing, and selling pharmaceuticals, the government issues a drug license. This type of license is required by all pharmacies in order to carry out various activities.</div>', '92', '2021-11-16 23:07:54', '2021-11-16 23:07:54'),
(152, 'overview', '<div><b><br></b></div><div><b>What is trade license?</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>A trade license is basically a permit or certificate that allows a company or individual to conduct business. This license is often issued by the state government for a certain municipal limit. The applicant will be able to operate a business in a certain territory with this license. The applicant must ensure that the business is conducted in accordance with the license\'s conditions.</div><div>This license prohibits the applicant from engaging in any other business than the one for which it was awarded. Aside from that, the license prevents the individual from securing the property or obtaining any legal rights to the place where the company is conducted.</div>', '93', '2021-11-16 23:13:52', '2021-11-16 23:13:52'),
(153, 'details', '<div><b><br></b></div><div><b>What are the major goals of a business license?</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>The government gives licenses to businesses in order to meet their needs. Aside from that, the trade license is issued for the reasons listed below:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • To control enterprises in a specific municipality or locality.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Ascertain that anti-competitive activities are not used within a specific municipality or locality.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • To keep track of a company\'s activity. Aside from that, local governments can keep an eye on a company\'s operations at all times.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The issuance of such a license would imply that a company is in accordance with the government.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Through this license, a local government can determine if the business is breaking any laws or producing a societal nuisance.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Consumers regard businesses with this license as more reputable. Customers would be more trusting of their offerings.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Businesses would not conduct any business on their residential premises if they obtained a license. As a result of this type of regulation, firms are regulated.</div>', '93', '2021-11-16 23:13:52', '2021-11-16 23:13:52'),
(154, 'requirement', '<div><b><br></b></div><div><b>Business Types that Require a Trade License</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>Any establishment that deals with food is considered a food business. This will also include a restaurant that serves and caters cuisine. Trade licenses are required for the following firms to operate:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Hotels, restaurants, and canteens are all examples of this type of establishment.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Shopping malls, theatres, and nightclubs</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Snack Shops, Bakeries, and Confectionery Shops</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Dairy requires a store, retailers, and any other food-serving establishment.</div>', '93', '2021-11-16 23:13:52', '2021-11-16 23:13:52'),
(155, 'listicles', '<div><b>Other Related Services to Trade Business</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>Any job or profession that includes providing services to individuals will need to obtain a certain type of license. This license is required for the following trades:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Salons and barbershops</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Internet parlours and cyber cafes</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Manufacturing Units of a Small Size</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Units of Medium Manufacturing</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Small-scale businesses</div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>Industries that make things</b></div><div>This license is also required for any industry that manufactures items. This license is required in the following industries:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Large Manufacturing Units&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Industries Medium-sized Manufacturing Units and Industries</div><div><br></div><div><b>Trade License Classification</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>Licenses are categorized into the following categories based on the amount of risk posed by the business:</div><div>Licensing with Low Risk</div><div>Any type of business that does not pose a high risk would be eligible for this type of license. Restaurants and other types of eateries usually take this license into consideration.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><b>License with a Medium Risk Level</b></div><div><br></div><div>Small and medium-sized businesses are the most common recipients of this sort of license.</div><div>License for High-Risk Activities</div><div>This sort of permit is typically given to industries and large-scale businesses. This type of business usually faces a greater danger of dealing with a variety of materials and substances. When compared to low and medium risk licenses, the monitoring levels on these premises are usually higher.</div>', '93', '2021-11-16 23:13:52', '2021-11-16 23:13:52'),
(156, 'regs', '<div><b>Advantages of Getting a Trade License?</b></div><div><br></div><div>The municipal authority issues traders a trade license that allows them to conduct business in a specific area. Trade licenses are necessary for monitoring business operations and assessing whether or not businesses are following the requirements.</div><div>It ensures that clients are not harmed by health difficulties as a result of bad company practices. It preserves the market\'s better goodwill. An increasing number of customers and investors are attracted to the registration of a trade license.</div><div>It is to ensure that the authority as well as the consumers are satisfied that the working procedures are carried out fairly and in accordance with the established rules and regulations.</div>', '93', '2021-11-16 23:13:52', '2021-11-16 23:13:52'),
(157, 'others', '<div><b>Application for a Trade License:</b> </div><div><br></div><div>Eligibility Criteria</div><div>To be qualified to apply for the aforementioned license, the candidate must meet the following requirements:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • A large candidate or individual is required. This indicates that the applicant must be over the age of eighteen.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • There should be no convictions or criminal records on the applicant\'s record.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The applicant\'s business must not be in violation of any current laws.</div>', '93', '2021-11-16 23:13:52', '2021-11-16 23:13:52'),
(158, 'guide', '<div><b>Required Documents List</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>At the time of completing the application form for a Delhi trade license, the following information or documents/records must be provided.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Individual proof of address and identity.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Affidavit</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The company\'s Certificate of Incorporation, MOA, and AOA.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Bank Statement and Cancelled Cheque</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The company\'s Certificate of Incorporation, MOA, and AOA.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Document of Legal Occupancy or allotment letter from the government agency\'s establishment/unit.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Documentary evidence of the start of a business.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Lease The constitution\'s deed</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Documentary evidence of the absence of unauthorized construction.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The land-owning agency\'s NOC (No Objection Certificate)</div><div>The procedure for obtaining a trade license</div><div>The following requirements must be met, depending on where the candidate is located:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The trade license certification must be applied for either online or offline. The candidate must fill out an application and attach the required documents for the online approach. The applicant must take all of the documents to the relevant authority using the offline approach (in person). The applicant must then complete the application form with the necessary information for the license.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Different states will have different processes for applying for a license depending on the applicant\'s needs. The government, on the other hand, has launched attempts to make all state systems computerized.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • To apply for an online trade license, the applicant must go to the specified website.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Following that, the applicant will receive a pop-up notification containing the terms and conditions that must be followed in order to obtain a trading license.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The applicant must agree the terms and conditions by clicking the accept button.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The applicant would next fill in the relevant information and facts about the trade license as the next stage in the procedure.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The online system for license registration offers a mode where electronic document authentication can be performed. The applicant must complete these tasks and submit the necessary documentation.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • After this procedure is completed, the applicant will receive confirmation of the trade license\'s successful registration.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The applicant will get confirmation of the application, and the license will be issued within eight to eleven working days.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • When opposed to rural locations, the procedure of obtaining a trade license in Metropolitan Cities is usually speedier.</div><div>Breach or Penalties for Failure to Acquire a License</div><div>If the applicant refuses to take the license, there are serious consequences:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Once the applicant has obtained a trade license, he or she must ensure that compliance is followed and maintained.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • If the applicant fails to get a trade license, the competent authorities may apply various penalties.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • If a business is created and operated without the necessary licenses, a penalty or charge must be paid.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • If noncompliance continues, the defaulter may be prosecuted.</div><div>Trade License Renewal</div><div>The license may be renewed if the following conditions are met:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • These licenses are typically renewed between January 1 and March 31 of each financial year.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • This license validity is for a period of one year.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • In India, the applicant must submit an application for a trade license.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The application must be submitted thirty days before to the certificate\'s expiration date.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Documents must be presented to the appropriate authority when the certificate is renewed.</div>', '93', '2021-11-16 23:13:52', '2021-11-16 23:13:52'),
(159, 'faq', '<div><b>Frequently asked questions:</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 1 How do you get a business license in India?</div><div>This license can be obtained by submitting an online application to the local government. An applicant cannot operate the business or provide the services supplied by the business without a license.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 2 How long does it takes in gettingt a business license?</div><div>The time it takes for this type of certification will vary depending on the municipality. The applicant will, however, acquire the certificate faster in a city than in a rural region.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 3 How can I get a new trade license if my current one expires?</div><div>If the license has expired, the applicant can submit an application for a trade license renewal. If not, the applicant must demonstrate the trade license to the appropriate municipal body.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 4 What are the consequences of failing to comply with the license\'s requirements?</div><div>The municipal corporation has the authority to impose the following penalties:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • License revocation in the event of non-compliance with the license\'s requirements&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Penalty for not adhering to the license\'s terms; or</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • In addition, the municipal government has the right to initiate criminal proceedings.</div><div><br></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 5 How do you renew a trade license?</div><div>The applicant will need to submit a license renewal application to the appropriate municipal authorities. However, this must be done at least one month before the license expires.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 6 Is it possible for a firm to apply for a license?</div><div>Yes, a business can submit an application for a trade license. The company must submit documents of incorporation, as well as additional information such as the Permanent Account Number (PAN).</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 7 What documentation must be supplied for the trading license to be renewed?</div><div>For renewal of the license, the applicant must submit the following documents:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Original copy of the trade license&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Property tax challans&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Property tax</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 8 Is a trade license required to operate a restaurant?</div><div>Yes, whatever area of company you\'re in, you\'ll need a Trade License. A trade license is required for every firm that transfers goods or services for money. A Food Establishment license is required before starting a restaurant.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 9 Is it required to reapply for a business license?</div><div>Renewal of the trade license is required.</div><div>10.Is it possible for an application to file a petition if their trade license is denied?</div><div>If an applicant is denied a Trade License for whatever reason, he or she may submit a petition to the Standing Committee along with a copy of the refusal letter.</div>', '93', '2021-11-16 23:13:52', '2021-11-16 23:13:52'),
(160, 'overview', '<div><b>What is trademark registration?</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>A trademark is the distinctive identification that distinguishes your organization, product, or service from the competition. A registered trademark is your company\'s intellectual property/intangible asset. It protects the time and effort you spend into winning the trust and loyalty of your customers.</div><div>The registration gives you the legal right to sue anyone who attempts to mimic your trademark and prevents others from using a similar trademark.</div><div>Trademarks are registered in India by –</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The Controller General of Patents, Designs, and Trademarks of the Indian Ministry of Industry and Commerce.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The Trademark Act of 1999 was used to register the trademark. Brand registration gives you the legal right to sue anyone who tries to use your trademark without permission. A person cannot use a trademark that is simlar to one that has already been registered.</div>', '94', '2021-11-16 23:19:31', '2021-11-16 23:19:31'),
(161, 'details', '<div><b>What is the benefit of registering a trademark?</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>Although registering a trademark is not required in order to use it, it adds tremendous value to a firm. When others try to portray their own goods and services as yours by adopting a brand that is similar to or identical to yours, a company\'s goodwill and image can be harmed. The following are some of the most important advantages of trademark registration:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • After the trademark is registered, the proprietor has the right to prevent someone from using that trademark that is similar to or identical to his without his prior permission.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Creates a correct perception of the product\'s genuine ownership and quality among the general audience.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Because the owner of a registered trademark can sue and recover damages from organizations that infringe on the trademark, it prevents others from copying and using it.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • A trademark registration reduces the chances of someone else claiming that your trademark infringes on theirs.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The right to use the TM emblem is granted to the owner.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • It serves as a warning to anyone considering filing a similar or identical trade mark in Singapore, as the Singapore trademark office will not register any confusingly similar marks. Additionally, when businesses consider adopting a mark that is similar to yours, your mark will display on the local Trade Marks Register.</div>', '94', '2021-11-16 23:19:31', '2021-11-16 23:19:31'),
(162, 'requirement', '<div><b>Documents needed to register a trademark</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>A trademark registration is an important practice for protecting a brand/business from unauthorized use and infringement.</div><div>The Government of India has simplified the trademark registration system over time to enable entrepreneurs to obtain trademark registration for their brands in a matter of months. The following are the various paperwork needed to register a trademark in India.</div><div>Note: Original documents are not required to be submitted throughout the trademark application registration process. The criterion can be met with scanned copies of the original documents.</div><div>Individuals and sole proprietorships must provide certain documents.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Ideally in black and white, a copy of the suggested logo (which is optional). If the logo is not provided, a trademark application for the word might be filed instead.&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Form 48, which has been duly signed. This document serves as an authorization for a Trademark Attorney to file a trademark registration application on the applicant\'s behalf.&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Copy of the individual applicant\'s or proprietor\'s identity evidence, such as a passport, Aadhar card, or PAN card.&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Copy of the person applicant\'s or proprietor\'s address evidence, which may include the most recent electricity bill, phone bill, etc.</div><div>Partnership / Company / LLP</div><div>The following documents must be submitted by the entrepreneur/applicant in the case of a partnership firm or an LLP:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • A scanned version of the logo (optional)</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Duly signed Form- 48</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Udyog Aadhar Registration Certificate</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Partnership Deed or the Incorporation Certificate</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Copy of identity proof of applicant</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Copy of address proof of signatory/ applicant</div><div>The following documents must be submitted by other applicants in a trademark registration.</div><div>In order to get trademark registration in India, applicants including those companies that doesn’t have an Udyog Aadhar number, should submit the following documentation.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The applicant must provide a copy of the logo.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Duly signed Form- 48</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Partnership Deed or the Incorporation Certificate</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Copy of identity proof of signatory.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The applicant must also provide an address proof.</div>', '94', '2021-11-16 23:19:31', '2021-11-16 23:19:31'),
(163, 'listicles', '<div><b>Who Can File a Trademark Application?</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>When a trademark is officially registered, the individual whose name appears on the Brand Registration form as the applicant is considered the brand\'s owner. Any individual, organization, or limited liability partnership can submit a trademark registration application.</div><div>What are the many sorts of trademark units?</div><div>Trademarks can be registered in India in a variety of formats, including logo, label, word mark, and device mark. As a result, deciding whether to register the trademark as a word mark or a logo is a tricky one.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Word mark</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>A word mark is the simplest of the other potential trademarks, and it represents the brand\'s name. For example, Jio or Britannia have merely trademarked the word, which is known as a word mark.</div><div>The term is self-registered using a word mark. After a trademark for a word mark is registered, the applicant has the absolute right to use and represent the word in any format or font, giving it broader protection that includes exclusive rights to the word as a whole and the ability to describe it in a variety of formats, regardless of style, for all goods and services associated with the mark.</div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>Logo</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>A logo, on the other hand, grants the trademark holder rights to a mix of pictures, words, and design when viewed as a whole. Nike, Adidas, and other brands come to mind. Furthermore, if the business logo is unmistakably recognizable by the public, the applicant may wish to file a trademark for that logo.</div><div>Composite Mark for a Logo</div><div>A business\'s brand name usually consists of both words and logos. For example, Jack &amp; Jones (a global garment company) has a complex logo composite mark that includes even the location of its label on the back of their jeans. In such cases, the best strategy to protect intellectual property is to file the trademark as both a word mark and a logo. However, because filing several trademark applications is a costly process, registering the trademark as a word mark is always recommended.</div>', '94', '2021-11-16 23:19:31', '2021-11-16 23:19:31'),
(164, 'regs', '<div><b>Trademark registration process</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>Step 1: Search the internet for a brand name that is \"wacky-enough\" to be registered as a trademark.</div><div>This is simply the quickest and most effective technique for any beginner to obtain a memorable, trendy, and intriguing company name. Choosing a weird and quirky brand name is a smart option because most generic names are already in use. Furthermore, deciding on a name necessitates a quick research procedure to verify that you are not selecting a brand name that is already in use. The best aspect is that you may develop a distinctive brand name for yourself by inventing or coining some words from a combination of generic phrases.</div><div>The second step is to prepare a trademark application.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • For online trademark registration, the following supporting papers must be presented with the application:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Proof of Business Registration: An identification proof of the company\'s directors and an address proof must be supplied based on your registered business (for example, sole proprietorship and so on). In the instance of a sole proprietorship, the proprietor\'s id evidence, such as a PAN card or an Aadhar card, could be submitted. In the case of businesses, however, the company\'s address evidence must be submitted.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • An electronic copy of the trademark.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The proposed mark\'s proof of claim (if applicable) can be utilized in another nation.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The applicant should sign a power of attorney.</div><div>Step 3: Submitting a trademark registration application</div><div>The two methods for filing the registration application are manual filing and e-filing (form TM-A). If you select \'manual filing,\' you must personally transport and handover your registration application to the Registrar Office of Trade Marks in major Indian cities such as Delhi, Mumbai, Kolkata, Ahmedabad, and Chennai. After then, you must wait at least 15 to 20 days to obtain the acknowledgment of receipt. However, if you use an e-filing system, you will obtain your receipt of acknowledgment on the government website very immediately.</div><div>Step 4: Examining the application process for a trademark</div><div>After you submit your application, the Registrar of Trademarks will review it to see if you followed all of the criteria and that your brand name is legal. Furthermore, the registration should not be similar to or identical to any existing or pending brands. This is why we recommended that you create a unique brand name!</div><div>Step 5: Your brand will be published in the Indian Trade Mark Journals.</div><div>The Registrar of Trademarks will publish your brand name in the Indian trademark journal following the examination procedure. This is the most significant element of the trademark registration, and no opposition should be filed within three months of the date of publication, i.e. 90 days (or 120 days in some situations). The Registrar of Trademarks will proceed with the issuance of a Trademark Registration Certificate if there is no opposition.</div><div>Step 6: Opposition to a Trademark</div><div>If a third party files an opposition within three months of the trademark being published in the trademarks journal, the Registrar of Trademarks will send you a copy of the opposition notice. Within months, you must respond to the opposition notice by filing a counter-statement. The trademark application will be regarded abandoned and rejected if you do not file a rebuttal statement within two months.</div><div>If no objection is filed within three months, this procedure will not apply to you, and your brand name will be accepted for issue of a Trademark Registration Certificate.</div><div>Step 7: Trademark Opposition Hearing</div><div>If there is no trademark opposition, you will not need to take this step.</div><div>If a third party opposes your trademark registration and you respond within two months, the Registrar of Trademarks will send a copy of your counter-statement to the third party opposing trademark registration.</div><div>You and the third party must both submit evidence in support of your case. Following the submission of evidence, the Registrar will hold a hearing for you and the third party. The Registrar will issue an order accepting or rejecting the trademark application after hearing both parties and examining the facts.</div><div>Step 8: The issuance of the trademark registration certificate</div><div>If no objection is filed within the 90-day period, the Registrar will accept your trademark application, or if your trademark application is accepted after a trademark opposition hearing. Wow! And the Registrar will issue the Registration Certificate with the Trademark Registry seal, which will be the greatest moment for you.</div><div>You can use the registered trademark symbol (®) with your brand name immediately after receiving your certificate.</div><div>As a result of this blog article, we believe that even a novice can comprehend everything about developing a brand name and effectively registering it.</div>', '94', '2021-11-16 23:19:31', '2021-11-16 23:19:31'),
