(167, 'faq', '<div><b><br></b></div><div><b>Frequently asked questions:</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 1 Is it possible for overseas applicants to register their trademarks in India?</div><div>An international trademark application may be filed through the applicant\'s trademark office under the Madrid Protocol (the Madrid Agreement Concerning the International Registration of Marks, dated 1891, which entered into force on December 1, 1995, and went into effect on April 1, 1996) The Office of Origin is another name for this trademark office. The application is received by the Office of Origin, which subsequently sends it to the WIPO.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 2 What is the definition of a trademark class?</div><div>In total goods and other services are divided into 45 categories by the Trademark Registry. Each class has a different set of goods and services, and you must identify which class(es) you\'re marketing on your trademark application. To register and protect the trademark, only those classes would be used.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 3 What types of trademark applications are most frequently rejected?</div><div>If your trademark is identical to an existing application, might be offensive to religious emotions, involves geographical names, or contains common words, it should be rejected. If it is likely to cause confusion, it will also be rejected.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 4 What if my trademark is already registered but in a different category?</div><div>You\'re still in luck if your brand name has already been registered, but under a different class. Your application is likely to be approved unless the brand is too well-known (such as McDonald\'s or Fiat).</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 5 What if someone holds a trademark on a similar term?</div><div>You can\'t seem to get the word out, but it\'s not all doom and gloom. Instead, you may create a distinctive logo for your company that includes the name. So there is a way out, however it is preferable to have a distinctive name.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 6 Is it necessary for me to file the trademark in my own name?</div><div>Many start-up founders register it in their personal names, whereas huge corporations choose to register it in the company\'s name. This is because a startup\'s future is never certain. The trademark would be valid regardless of the state of the firm if it was owned by the founder. In this scenario, however, a trademark license agreement is required.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 7 How long will it take for my trademark to be approved?</div><div>The approval of your trademark can take anything from 6 months to a year.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 8 Is it possible to transfer a trademark to someone else?</div><div>A trademark can be passed down from one person to the next. The transfer processing cost will vary depending on the state of the mark.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 9 In India, how much does it cost to trademark and register a company\'s name and logo?</div><div>For each type of use, the government fees for filing an online application for trademark registration are Rs. 4500/- for small businesses and Rs. 9000/- for large businesses.</div><div>10.What does it indicate when my trademark application is marked as \"Objected\"?</div><div>When the Examiner raises certain concerns about the trademark\'s registrability, the status changes to \"Objected.\"</div>', '94', '2021-11-16 23:19:31', '2021-11-16 23:19:31'),
(168, 'overview', '<div><b>What is IATA Registration?</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>In India, one of the most important sectors is travel and tourism. The burgeoning middle class has increased demand for travel and tourist products, making the travel industry one of India\'s fastest-growing sectors. For many entrepreneurs, becoming a travel agency is a great alternative, and having IATA registration can help increase revenue.</div><div>The following registrations are required to start a travel agency business:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 1 GST registration</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 2 Business Registration, which may be of the following types.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Private limited company; or</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • A limited liability partnership; or</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • A one-person company</div><div>Registration with the International Air Transport Association (IATA) is not required to work as a travel agency. Having an IATA registration, on the other hand, can demonstrate to potential clients and vendors that the company is a legitimate travel agency, resulting in increased revenue and credibility.</div>', '95', '2021-11-16 23:22:26', '2021-11-16 23:22:26'),
(169, 'details', '<div><b><br></b></div><div><b>Benefits of IATA Registration:</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>The IATA accreditation streamlines the business interaction between travel agents and airlines. More than 60,000 IATA travel agents sell $220 billion in plane tickets on behalf of 250 IATA airline members all around the world. The following are some of the advantages of IATA membership:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • With a single Sales Agency Agreement that enables the selling of international and/or domestic tickets, you can have access to IATA airline members.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The IATA Billing and Settlement Plan is now online, providing a consumer interface for billing and payments between brokers, airlines, and transport companies.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The \"IATA Numeric Code\" provides a unique identifier for the global travel business.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • The \"IATA Accredited Agent\" badge is displayed on-premises and on the website, offering visibility and credibility.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Agents are eligible for the IATA/IATAN ID Card, which grants them access to over 1000 suppliers\' exclusive offers.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Standardized protocols to ensure that the airlines are treated fairly.</div>', '95', '2021-11-16 23:22:26', '2021-11-16 23:22:26'),
(170, 'requirement', '<div><b><br></b></div><div><b>Requirements for IATA Registration</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>The following four factors are assessed when applying to become an IATA Accredited Agent:</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Agent staff credentials and financial history</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Location identification and accessibility</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Procedures and security</div><div>In the IATA certification procedure, the applicant\'s financial record and financial standing play a significant role. The following are the financial criteria for IATA registration application financial evaluation in India (all financial information utilized in the financial criteria will be collected from the Agent\'s Audited Accounts):</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Positive Net Equity is required.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Net equity must be larger than 0.5 when compared to long-term debt and other long-term liabilities.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Except in unusual situations, EBITDA (Earnings Before Interest, Taxes, Depreciation, Amortization, and Extraordinary Items) must be positive.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • EBITDA must surpass interest payable by a factor of at least two, preferably three.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; • Total liabilities must never be more than total assets.</div><div>Furthermore, for the first two years as an Agent, all Agents must furnish financial security. Any Financial Security required to be provided to IATA must be received by IATA and confirmed to IATA by written confirmation received directly from the third party supporting the Financial Security that the Financial Security was issued and is valid before an Agent can be accredited or continue to be accredited. To be accredited, all travel agents must furnish Financial Security in the amount of USD 50,000.</div>', '95', '2021-11-16 23:22:26', '2021-11-16 23:22:26'),
(171, 'listicles', '<div><b><br></b></div><div><b>Are you interested in becoming an IATA Agent?</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>The \'Travel Agent Handbook,\' which is available, is a good place to start for any aspiring IATA member. After completing all of the local criteria outlined in that book, the agent should choose the country of application and submit it according to the instructions outlined in that company\'s Application Guide. The accreditation fee, as previously indicated, varies by area. IATA will contact applicants in Europe, the Middle East, and Africa for payment once their application has been accepted. The IATA\'s pledge of allegiance to the aviation sector is taken at face value.</div>', '95', '2021-11-16 23:22:26', '2021-11-16 23:22:26'),
